1d57131a [deepseek-v4] #It sounds like you’re testing the Discord bot integration and suspect the TCP connections aren’t
1d57131a [deepseek-v4] #working. Let’s isolate the common issues.
1d57131b [deepseek-v4] #
1d57131b [deepseek-v4] #Quick checks
1d57131b [deepseek-v4] #
1d57131b [deepseek-v4] #1. Is the Discord bot online?
1d57131c [deepseek-v4] #   In the terminal running `sloppybot.ts`, you should see `sloppy 0.10 🦜 splurt:...` and then
1d57131c [deepseek-v4] #`[SLOPPY] discordClient online <bot name>`. If not, either the token is missing (env `DISCORD_BOT`)
1d57131c [deepseek-v4] #or the bot is not invited to the server.
1d57131c [deepseek-v4] #
1d57131c [deepseek-v4] #2. Are the TCP ports free?
1d57131d [deepseek-v4] #   The fountain (relay) listens on 8081, 8082, 8083 when `listen` config flag is enabled. The bot
1d57131d [deepseek-v4] #connects to port 8081 by default.
1d57131d [deepseek-v4] #   Run `netstat -an | findstr :8081` (Windows) or `lsof -i :8081` (macOS/Linux) to see if something
1d57131d [deepseek-v4] #is already listening.
1d57131e [deepseek-v4] #   If you start the fountain after the bot (or vice versa), you’ll get `Address already in use`
1d57131e [deepseek-v4] #errors (check stderr of both processes).
1d57131e [deepseek-v4] #
1d57131e [deepseek-v4] #3. Logs from the bot (sloppybot)
1d57131e [deepseek-v4] #   It writes debug messages to `console.error` (splurt). Look for lines like:
1d57131f [deepseek-v4] #   - `connected with noDelay localhost:8081` – connection succeeded.
1d57131f [deepseek-v4] #   - `Connection Refused` – the fountain is not listening yet.
1d57131f [deepseek-v4] #   - `Connection Error` – something else (e.g., firewall, port blocked).
1d57131f [deepseek-v4] #
1d57131f [deepseek-v4] #4. Logs from the fountain
1d571320 [deepseek-v4] #   When a TCP client connects, `slopprompt.ts` prints:
1d571320 [deepseek-v4] #   `[PROMPT] listening for slop <port> <name>`
1d571320 [deepseek-v4] #   and later:
1d571320 [deepseek-v4] #   `connection received for <name>`
1d571320 [deepseek-v4] #   If you see these, the link is up.
1d571321 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571321 [deepseek-v4] #Common pitfalls
1d571321 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571321 [deepseek-v4] #- Double‑listen in `slopprompt.ts`
1d571321 [deepseek-v4] #  In `slopPrompt()` it calls `listenPort(8081...)` again, even if `listenService()` already opened
1d571322 [deepseek-v4] #the port. This will fail silently (or throw) because the port is already bound. I recommend
1d571322 [deepseek-v4] #removing the listen calls inside `slopPrompt` – the listeners should only be created once, either
1d571322 [deepseek-v4] #in `listenService()` or inside `slopPrompt`, not both.
1d571322 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571323 [deepseek-v4] #- Bot‑fountain ordering
1d571323 [deepseek-v4] #  The bot waits 20 seconds before trying to connect. If the fountain starts later, the bot will
1d571323 [deepseek-v4] #keep retrying (only once, unfortunately). Consider adding a reconnection loop in
1d571324 [deepseek-v4] #`connectFountain()`.
1d571324 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571324 [deepseek-v4] #- Firewall / antivirus
1d571324 [deepseek-v4] #  On Windows, Deno may need explicit permission to listen on localhost ports. Check Windows
1d571325 [deepseek-v4] #Defender notifications.
1d571325 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571325 [deepseek-v4] #- Missing `listen` config flag
1d571325 [deepseek-v4] #  In `relay.ts`, `listenService()` and `acceptThread()` are only called if `roha.config.listen` is
1d571326 [deepseek-v4] #true. Make sure you set that flag (e.g., `/config listen` command) before trying to use the bot.
1d571326 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571326 [deepseek-v4] #Next steps
1d571326 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571327 [deepseek-v4] #1. Start the fountain first with `listen` enabled, then start the bot (or vice versa).
1d571327 [deepseek-v4] #2. Watch stderr of both processes for any error lines.
1d571327 [deepseek-v4] #3. Try a simple TCP test – use `telnet localhost 8081` or `nc localhost 8081` to see if the
1d571328 [deepseek-v4] #fountain accepts connections.
1d571328 [deepseek-v4] #4. If you see `connection received` on the fountain side but no messages flowing, check that the
1d571328 [deepseek-v4] #bot is actually `@mentioning` the bot user in the Discord channel (the bot only responds to
1d571328 [deepseek-v4] #mentions in the `openChannel` – by default channel ID `1473539274384211999`).
1d571328 [deepseek-v4] #
1d571329 [deepseek-v4] #Once you have the error messages (if any), share them and we can drill down.
1d571329 [deepseek-v4] #
