1d6728d5 [deepseek-v4] #Thanks for sharing your codebase. I've reviewed the four files you provided: `relay.ts`,
1d6728d5 [deepseek-v4] #`slopprompt.ts`, `sloppybot.ts`, `slopsearch.ts`, and `deno.json`. Here are my observations:
1d6728d6 [deepseek-v4] #
1d6728d6 [deepseek-v4] #Overall Structure
1d6728d6 [deepseek-v4] #- Well-modularized – Separates console input handling (`slopprompt.ts`), Discord
1d6728d6 [deepseek-v4] #integration (`sloppybot.ts`), web search (`slopsearch.ts`), and the core `relay.ts`.
1d6728d7 [deepseek-v4] #- TypeScript used with Deno, using ES modules and JSR/npm dependencies.
1d6728d7 [deepseek-v4] #- Custom emoji/Unicode style – Heavy use of decorative Unicode characters, custom
1d6728d7 [deepseek-v4] #shortcodes, and wide/narrow glyph handling.
1d6728d7 [deepseek-v4] #
1d6728d8 [deepseek-v4] #Key Design Patterns
1d6728d8 [deepseek-v4] #1. Recursive relay loop – `relay` function recursively processes tool calls, then continues
1d6728d8 [deepseek-v4] #the conversation. This is a clean pattern for handling multi-turn function calls.
1d6728d8 [deepseek-v4] #2. History management – `rohaHistory` array with push/pop session stack; `squashMessages`
1d6728d9 [deepseek-v4] #to merge consecutive same-role entries.
1d6728d9 [deepseek-v4] #3. Multi‑provider adapter – Each provider (OpenAI, DeepSeek, Google, Anthropic) has its own
1d6728d9 [deepseek-v4] #connection/chat method via `connectAccount()` and a unified `chat.completions.create` interface.
1d6728d9 [deepseek-v4] #4. File sharing – `shareSlop`, `commitShares`, `shareBlob` handle local file scanning,
1d6728da [deepseek-v4] #dedup by hash, and attaching as text/images to the conversation.
1d6728da [deepseek-v4] #
1d6728da [deepseek-v4] #Potential Issues / Notes
1d6728da [deepseek-v4] #- Error handling in `relay` – Many `catch` blocks return `spend` early but do not rethrow
1d6728db [deepseek-v4] #or signal failure to the caller. This could mask API errors.
1d6728db [deepseek-v4] #- Performance – The `readNamedConnection` and `receivePromises` map may leak entries if
1d6728db [deepseek-v4] #clients disconnect without proper cleanup (though you do delete on error).
1d6728db [deepseek-v4] #- Race condition – In `slopPrompt`, the `receivePromises` are populated inside the loop;
1d6728dc [deepseek-v4] #but if a connection closes right after `accept`, the promise may never resolve. Adding a timeout or
1d6728dc [deepseek-v4] #cleanup could help.
1d6728dc [deepseek-v4] #- Memory – `rxBuffer` of 1 MB per connection is fine, but multiple bots could add up.
1d6728dc [deepseek-v4] #- `discordStringWidth` – Returns floats like 1.5, 2.5; used for padding calculation – be
1d6728dd [deepseek-v4] #careful with integer vs. float comparisons in `boxCells`.
1d6728dd [deepseek-v4] #
1d6728dd [deepseek-v4] #New/Different Aspects
1d6728dd [deepseek-v4] #- The `responses` endpoint handling (OpenAI’s new `/v1/responses`) is a recent addition –
1d6728de [deepseek-v4] #good forward compatibility.
1d6728de [deepseek-v4] #-  Thinking mode with `thinking: { type: "adaptive" }` for Anthropic is correctly
1d6728df [deepseek-v4] #implemented.
1d6728df [deepseek-v4] #-  Gemini TTS via `geminiSay` and `saveGeminiSpeech` – novel integration using the preview
1d6728df [deepseek-v4] #TTS model.
1d6728df [deepseek-v4] #- The shortcode system in `slopprompt.ts` (colon‑to‑emoji mapping) is a nice UX touch.
1d6728e0 [deepseek-v4] #- Deno tasks in `deno.json` show multiple bot instances run concurrently – seems like a
1d6728e0 [deepseek-v4] #multi‑bot architecture.
1d6728e0 [deepseek-v4] #
1d6728e0 [deepseek-v4] #Overall, this is a sophisticated research tool. If you're looking for specific improvements (e.g.,
1d6728e1 [deepseek-v4] #streaming responses, better error recovery, or documentation), let me know. Otherwise, it looks
1d6728e1 [deepseek-v4] #functional and well‑considered.
1d6728e1 [deepseek-v4] #
