1d818fee [roha] [ASSISTANT] {"role":"assistant","mut":"deepseek-v4","emoji":"🐋","name":"deepseek-v4-flash","content":"Based on your shared session, I see a few significant problems in the relay system that cause degraded operation:\n\n**1. Unnecessary raw byte echo broadcasts to all bots**\n\nIn `slopprompt.ts`, `readNamedConnection` logs raw byte arrays via `echo()`:\n```typescript\necho(\"[STATUS] readNamedConnection\",name,n,bytes);\n```\nThis `echo()` goes through the output buffer and gets broadcast to all connected slop clients. You can see the effect in `output2.txt`:\n```\n[STATUS] readNamedConnection connection0 88 123,34,109,101,115,115,97,103,101,115,34,58,91...\n```\nThis should use `echoInfo()` instead, which bypasses the broadcast pipeline.\n\n**2. Stale receive promises accumulate without cleanup**\n\nIn `slopprompt.ts`, `receivePromises[name]` is set after each read but never removed on error or disconnection:\n```typescript\nreceivePromises[name] = receiver;\n```\nWhen a connection returns `source` (either success or error), the promise is overwritten but the connection object may be invalid. The `delete receivePromises[name]` call only runs in the success path. If the connection errors, the throw at line:\n```typescript\nthrow(error); // this will cause a crash\n```\nterminates the entire prompt loop, bringing down the relay.\n\n**3. Connection error handling throws instead of recovering**\n\nWhen a bot connection has an error, `readNamedConnection` returns `{source: connection, error, name}`, but the handler in `slopPrompt` throws rather than cleaning up and retrying.\n\n**4. Duplicate echoInfo calls on every bot read**\n\nIn `relay.ts`, the `readNamedConnection` line:\n```typescript\necho(\"[STATUS] readNamedConnection\", name, n, bytes);\n```\nlogs twice for the same message — once with `readNamedConnection 90 connection0` (just name and length) and once with the full byte dump. The two log statements appear in different places in the code.\n\n**5. `remoteBuffer` processes stale entries silently**\n\nIn `relay.ts`, `remoteBuffer` collects overridden `console.error` calls. The flush function processes them:\n```typescript\nfor (const {line, from} of remoteBuffer) {\n    // muted on public channels\n    //      send.push(line);\n    // dont share just log remote chatter\n    //      rohaPush(line,from);\n    await logForge(line,from);\n}\n```\nThe code says \"dont share\" but still writes every error to forge.log. This can fill the log quickly with chatter messages that should be filtered.\n\n**Suggested fixes:**\n\nFor issue 1 — change `echo` to `echoInfo` in `readNamedConnection`:\n```typescript\nif (n == null) {\n    echoInfo(\"[STATUS] readNamedConnection close\", name);\n    return {source: connection};\n}\nechoInfo(\"[STATUS] readNamedConnection bytes\", name, n);\n```\n\nFor issue 2 — clean up on both success and error paths, and remove the throw:\n```typescript\nif (source) {\n    delete receivePromises[name];\n    if (error) {\n        echoInfo(\"[PROMPT] connection error\", name, error.message);\n        slopConnections.delete(name);\n        continue;\n    }\n    // ... process receive data ...\n}\n```\n\nFor issue 5 — filter `remoteBuffer` to exclude connection chatter:\n```typescript\nfor (const {line, from} of remoteBuffer) {\n    if (line.includes(\"readNamedConnection\") || line.includes(\"connection\")) continue;\n    await logForge(line, from);\n}\n```\n\nThe system is fundamentally working — messages flow from Discord through to the model and back. But these debug-logging and error-handling issues create noise and risk crashes.","elapsed":28.675433299999998,"price":0.010890292000000001}
