1dab3b9e [deepseek-v4] #(luma) signal this works because the pin level can be set directly while the direction is held as
1dab3b9f [deepseek-v4] #output. The colour burst, however, requires toggling a subcarrier frequency, which the chroma
1dab3b9f [deepseek-v4] #program likely does with `out pindirs, 9/8` – a technique that relies on toggling direction
1dab3b9f [deepseek-v4] #while the pin output is high (or low) to create a crude waveform. If the mono version uses the same
1dab3b9f [deepseek-v4] #GPIO pin(s) for both sync and video, the direction approach may work, but for colour you need
