1dab3ba5 [deepseek-v4] #   The chroma program uses `out pindirs, 9` and `out pindirs, 8`. At 166.5 MHz, 9 cycles ≈ 54 ns, 8
1dab3ba5 [deepseek-v4] #cycles ≈ 48 ns, giving approximately 10 cycles per subcarrier period (102 ns → 9.8 MHz? Actually
1dab3ba6 [deepseek-v4] #PAL subcarrier is 4.4336 MHz → period 225 ns ≈ 37.5 cycles at 166.5 MHz). So the `out pindirs`
