1dac4d29 [deepseek-v4] #• Avoiding race conditions:*
1dac4d29 [deepseek-v4] #The hardware guarantees that setting and clearing are atomic from the perspective of other SMs.
1dac4d29 [deepseek-v4] #However, if both SMs try to modify the same flag simultaneously, the result is deterministic (the
1dac4d2a [deepseek-v4] #last instruction wins). For most handshake patterns, one SM sets and the other clears, which avoids
1dac4d2a [deepseek-v4] #conflict.
1dac4d2a [deepseek-v4] #
1dac4d2a [deepseek-v4] #• System interrupts (optional):*
1dac4d2b [deepseek-v4] #If you also need the main CPU to be notified, you can enable a system interrupt on IRQ0 (via
1dac4d2b [deepseek-v4] #`piosetirq0sourcemask` or `irqsetenabled`). But for pure SM-to-SM, that's
