1dac640f [gemini-3.1-pro] #Here is the breakdown of the timing:
1dac640f [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dac640f [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Color Subcarrier Frequency (F_sc): 4.43361875 MHz
1dac640f [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Total Line Duration: 64 microseconds (μ s)
1dac6410 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Active Line Duration: Approximately 52 μ s (the remaining 12 μ s is horizontal blanking,
1dac6410 [gemini-3.1-pro] #including the front porch, sync pulse, and color burst)
1dac6410 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dac6410 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Calculating the cycles:*
1dac6411 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Total line: 64 μ s × 4.43361875 \text MHz = \mathbf283.75 color clocks per full line.
1dac6411 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Active line: 52 μ s × 4.43361875 \text MHz \approx \mathbf230.55 color clocks for the
1dac6411 [gemini-3.1-pro] #visible portion.
1dac6411 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dac6412 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Implementing this on PIO:*
1dac6412 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Because state machines require integer counts for loop iterations and delays, you cannot output
1dac6412 [gemini-3.1-pro] #fractional clocks directly. When generating composite video with a microcontroller, it is standard
1dac6412 [gemini-3.1-pro] #practice to run the PIO clock at a multiple of the color subcarrier frequency to allow for precise
1dac6413 [gemini-3.1-pro] #color phase control (which dictates the hue).
1dac6413 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dac6413 [gemini-3.1-pro] #A very common approach is to run the system or PIO clock at 4 × F_sc (17.734475 MHz).
1dac6413 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dac6414 [gemini-3.1-pro] #At a 4 × F_sc clock rate:
1dac6414 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Total line: 283.75 × 4 = \mathbf1135 PIO clock cycles.
1dac6414 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Active line: 230.55 × 4 \approx \mathbf922 PIO clock cycles (often rounded to a
1dac6414 [gemini-3.1-pro] #convenient number of pixels for the frame buffer, such as 720 or 768, padded with border timing).
1dac6415 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dac6415 [gemini-3.1-pro] #The exact number of active clocks you choose to send from your PIO will depend on your desired
1dac6415 [gemini-3.1-pro] #horizontal resolution and how much overscan you wish to include in your visible area.
1dac6415 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
