1dacefa0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #A Pro-Tip for the 2-Pin Hardware
1dacefa0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Pin A (High weight): Connect to the 100Ω resistor.
1dacefa0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Pin B (Low weight): Connect to the 330Ω resistor.
1dacefa1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• By toggling both, you get a 4-level DAC (0, 1, 2, 3).
1dacefa1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• The Pattern: For a sine wave, you would push patterns like `00, 01, 11, 10` into the
1dacefa1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #FIFO. This will look like a "staircase" that the filter will smooth into a beautiful,
1dacefa1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #low-distortion subcarrier.
1dacefa2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dacefa2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• This is a significant step up in signal quality.* By using the 2-pin approach, you
1dacefa2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #essentially eliminate the high-frequency switching noise that usually plagues simple bit-banged
1dacefa2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #video.
