1dad3b6b [gemini-3.1-lite] #Implementation Notes:
1dad3b6c [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dad3b6c [gemini-3.1-lite] #1.  DMA Integration (Recommended):
1dad3b6c [gemini-3.1-lite] #    Because you are driving video, the CPU will likely be too slow to feed the FIFO manually
1dad3b6c [gemini-3.1-lite] #line-by-line. Use a DMA channel to transfer the buffer to the PIO `TX` register.
1dad3b6d [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   Set the DMA `TREQ` to the PIO `DREQ` for the specific state machine.
1dad3b6d [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   Use a circular buffer if you are generating dynamic content.
1dad3b6d [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dad3b6d [gemini-3.1-lite] #2.  Bit Packing:
1dad3b6e [gemini-3.1-lite] #    The PIO `out pins, 1` instruction consumes 1 bit per cycle. If you are sending `uint32_t` from
