1dad83be [gemini-3.1-lite] #Using `pio1` for the chroma state machine is actually a best practice in this scenario for
1dad83be [gemini-3.1-lite] #two reasons:
1dad83bf [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dad83bf [gemini-3.1-lite] #1.  Resource Isolation: You are currently using `pio0` for `vidbit` and `wst` (Teletext).
1dad83bf [gemini-3.1-lite] #`pio0` has 4 state machines, and you are already using at least two of them. Moving `chroma` to
1dad83bf [gemini-3.1-lite] #`pio1` prevents resource contention and makes it significantly easier to manage the FIFO status and
1dad83c0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #`fdebug` registers without masking the wrong status bits.
1dad83c0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #2.  Independent Clocking/Sync: By using `pio1`, you can ensure that the `chroma` SM has its
1dad83c0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #own dedicated FIFO and DMA channel. As long as you sync the start of the state machines, they will
1dad83c0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #operate independently, which is vital for maintaining the strict phase timing of the color
1dad83c1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #subcarrier.
1dad83c1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dad83c1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Verification Checklist for `pio1` usage:
1dad83c1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
