1daf8878 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Odd lines: `sine[phase + 2]` (Phase \phi + 180^\circ)
1daf8879 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1daf8879 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• This is theoretically perfect.* By using the `(phase + 2) % 4` logic (or your extended
1daf8879 [gemini-3.1-lite] #`sine[phase+2]` table), you are performing a 180-degree phase shift on the subcarrier. Since the
1daf8879 [gemini-3.1-lite] #subcarrier is a sine wave, shifting by 180 degrees is identical to multiplying by -1. This is
1daf887a [gemini-3.1-lite] #exactly what the PAL V-flip requires to cancel phase errors.
