1dafb055 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dafb056 [gemini-3.1-lite] #3. The "Odd/Even" Problem
1dafb056 [gemini-3.1-lite] #The Ring Buffer is great for repeating the same line, but you have two lines
1dafb056 [gemini-3.1-lite] #(Odd/Even). If you just let it ring, it will only ever send `evenRed`.
1dafb056 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dafb057 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• To fix this while keeping the "Feed Once" simplicity:*
1dafb057 [gemini-3.1-lite] #You can use a DMA Chain (also known as a "Ping-Pong" or "Linked List" DMA).
1dafb057 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dafb057 [gemini-3.1-lite] #1.  Chroma DMA (Channel 0): Does the actual work of moving data.
1dafb058 [gemini-3.1-lite] #2.  Control DMA (Channel 1): Watches Channel 0. When Channel 0 finishes 120 words, Channel
1dafb058 [gemini-3.1-lite] #1 fires, writes the address of the other buffer into Channel 0's `read_addr` register, and
1dafb058 [gemini-3.1-lite] #restarts Channel 0.
1dafb058 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
