1dbb2c77 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dbb2c77 [gemini-3.1-pro] #1. Timing Fundamentals
1dbb2c77 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Based on your system clock and PIO divider:
1dbb2c78 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• System Clock: 166.5 MHz
1dbb2c78 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Chroma PIO Clock: 166.5 MHz / 2.3471 ≈ 70.938 MHz (14.1 ns per PIO cycle)
1dbb2c78 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Chroma Loop: 4 PIO cycles per 2-bit sample = 56.4 ns
1dbb2c78 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Subcarrier Cycle: 4 samples = 16 PIO cycles = 225.5 ns (4.4336 MHz, perfect for PAL)
1dbb2c79 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• One 32-bit DMA Word: 16 samples = 64 PIO cycles ≈ 0.902 µs
1dbb2c79 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1dbb2c79 [gemini-3.1-pro] #2. Offset from Porch (Breezeway)
1dbb2c79 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Your `vidbit` state machine triggers `irq 4` at the exact start of the back porch. The
1dbb2c7a [gemini-3.1-pro] #`chroma` state machine catches this and incurs the following delays before outputting the first
1dbb2c7a [gemini-3.1-pro] #word:
