1dbe32a2 [kimi-k2.6] #- Interlace vs. progressive: In non-lace mode the chroma ring buffer alternates even/odd
1dbe32a2 [kimi-k2.6] #burst phases every line because the DMA just streams through the 128-word table. Most PAL decoders
1dbe32a2 [kimi-k2.6] #will still lock, but if you see Hanover-bar artefacts on a progressive frame you can double the
