1dbe5e62 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Required Delay: 5.7 µs × 166.5 = 949.05 cycles.
1dbe5e62 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe5e62 [gemini-3.1-lite] #2. The Current Cycle Budget
1dbe5e62 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Let's trace the cycles in `vidbit.pio` from the trigger to the `wst` start:
1dbe5e63 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe5e63 [gemini-3.1-lite] #1.  `vidbit` IRQ Latency:
1dbe5e63 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   `irq set 0` executes.
1dbe5e63 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   `set y, 28` (1 cycle).
1dbe5e64 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   `backporchloop`: `jmp y--, backporchloop [31]` runs 29 times. Each loop is 32
1dbe5e64 [gemini-3.1-lite] #cycles. Total: 29 × 32 = 928 cycles.
1dbe5e64 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   Total `vidbit` delay before the SM finishes the back porch: 929 cycles.
1dbe5e64 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe5e65 [gemini-3.1-lite] #2.  `wst` Startup Latency:
1dbe5e65 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   `wait 1 irq 0`: Latches on the cycle the IRQ is set.
1dbe5e65 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   `irq clear 0`: 1 cycle.
1dbe5e65 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   `out x, 32`: 1 cycle.
1dbe5e66 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   `jmp !x start [16]`: 1 cycle + 16 delay = 17 cycles.
1dbe5e66 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   Total `wst` overhead: 19 cycles.
1dbe5e66 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe5e66 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Current Total:* 929 + 19 = 948 cycles.
1dbe5e67 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Result: You are at ~948 cycles, which is 5.69 µs. This is remarkably close to
1dbe5e67 [gemini-3.1-lite] #your target of 5.7 µs.
