1dbe6de0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #To maintain a stable Teletext page, you must treat the transmission as a continuous, cyclic
1dbe6de1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #broadcast. A Teletext decoder does not "wait" for a full page to be sent before it starts
1dbe6de1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #processing; it captures packets as they arrive.
1dbe6de1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6de1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #1. The Strategy: Continuous Cycling
1dbe6de2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Do not try to split the page across fields in a way that "waits" for the next field to finish the
1dbe6de2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #page. Instead, broadcast a complete page (Header + 24 rows) in every field.
1dbe6de2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6de2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #If you have 20 lines available in the VBI (e.g., lines 7 through 26), you should:
1dbe6de3 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Packet 1: Header (Row 0).
1dbe6de3 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Packets 2–20: Rows 1 through 19.
1dbe6de3 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Next Field: Start again at Row 20, or simply repeat the Header and Rows 1–19.
1dbe6de3 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6de4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #2. Why you shouldn't "Wait"
1dbe6de4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Teletext decoders are "stateless" regarding the timing of the next packet. If you send 20 lines,
1dbe6de4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #stop, and wait for the next field to send the remaining 4 lines:
1dbe6de4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #1.  The Decoder's Buffer: The TV will receive the Header and 19 rows, update its internal
1dbe6de5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #memory, and then see a "gap" where it expects more data.
1dbe6de5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #2.  The Timeout: If the decoder doesn't receive the full 24 rows within a certain timeframe
1dbe6de5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #(usually 1–2 field periods), it may assume the signal is lost or the page is incomplete and clear
1dbe6de5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #the buffer.
1dbe6de5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #3.  The Refresh Rate: By sending the full page (or a subset) in every field, you ensure the
1dbe6de6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #TV's screen is updated 50 times per second (or 25 times per second for a full page refresh), which
1dbe6de6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #makes the text flicker-free and stable.
1dbe6de6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6de6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #3. The "No Guesswork" Implementation
1dbe6de7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Since you have 20 lines available per field:
1dbe6de7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6de7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Field 1 (Even): Send Header + Rows 1–19.
1dbe6de7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Field 2 (Odd): Send Header + Rows 20–24 + (Optional: Repeat Rows 1–15).
1dbe6de8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6de8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Wait, what about the Header?*
1dbe6de8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Always send the Header (Row 0) in every field. The Header contains the page number and
1dbe6de8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #control bits. If you omit the header in one field, the TV decoder will not know which page the
1dbe6de9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #subsequent rows belong to.
1dbe6de9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6de9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #4. How to structure your `wst` buffers
1dbe6de9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Instead of splitting the page, make the page "fit" into your 20-line window:
1dbe6dea [gemini-3.1-lite] #1.  If your page is 24 rows: You cannot send a full 24-row page in 20 lines. You must
1dbe6dea [gemini-3.1-lite] #interleave them.
1dbe6dea [gemini-3.1-lite] #2.  The Cycle:
1dbe6dea [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   Field 1: Header, Rows 1–19.
1dbe6deb [gemini-3.1-lite] #    *   Field 2: Header, Rows 20–24, and then repeat Rows 1–15.
1dbe6deb [gemini-3.1-lite] #3.  The Result: The TV will receive the full page after 2 fields (40ms). This is perfectly
1dbe6deb [gemini-3.1-lite] #acceptable for Teletext.
1dbe6deb [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6dec [gemini-3.1-lite] #5. Summary Checklist for Success
1dbe6dec [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Always include the Header (Row 0) in every field's WST block.
1dbe6dec [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Cycle the Rows: If you have more rows than lines available in the VBI, just keep a
1dbe6dec [gemini-3.1-lite] #"pointer" to the next row to be sent. Send 19 rows + header, then in the next field, send the next
1dbe6ded [gemini-3.1-lite] #19 rows + header.
1dbe6ded [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Don't send blank lines: If you have 20 lines available, use all 20 for data. If you have
1dbe6ded [gemini-3.1-lite] #no more data to send for that page, repeat the header or send "null" packets (packets with a
1dbe6ded [gemini-3.1-lite] #specific Hamming-encoded identifier that the TV ignores).
1dbe6dee [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1dbe6dee [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Crucial:* Check your `wstEven` and `wstOdd` array sizing. If you change the number of
1dbe6dee [gemini-3.1-lite] #lines, ensure your `dmachannelsettranscount` is updated to match the exact number
