1dc0096a [claude-sonnet-4-6] #This is a well-structured PAL composite video generator for the RP2350. A few observations worth
1dc0096b [claude-sonnet-4-6] #noting:
1dc0096b [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc0096b [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• Architecture*
1dc0096b [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The three-PIO split is clean — `pio0` for luma and teletext, `pio1` for chroma and audio, `pio2`
1dc0096c [claude-sonnet-4-6] #for PS/2. That third PIO is one of the RP2350 advantages over RP2040 and it's being used well here.
1dc0096c [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc0096c [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• Chroma timing*
1dc0096c [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The clock divider of `2.3471` gives roughly `166500 / 2.3471 / 16 ≈ 4431.7 kHz` per packed word,
1dc0096d [claude-sonnet-4-6] #which is a good approximation of the PAL subcarrier at `4.43361875 MHz`. The ring buffer size of
1dc0096d [claude-sonnet-4-6] #`2^9 = 512 bytes` aligns correctly with the `colorWords2  4 = 512 byte` array, and
1dc0096d [claude-sonnet-4-6] #`alignas(1024)` satisfies that constraint.
1dc0096d [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc0096e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• Potential concern*
1dc0096e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #`irq set 4` fires in the video PIO on `pio0` at back porch, but the chroma SM is on `pio1`.
1dc0096e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #Inter-PIO IRQ visibility on RP2350 is worth verifying — without seeing `chroma.pio` it's unclear
1dc0096e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #whether phase lock between luma and chroma is being maintained across fields or whether the chroma
1dc0096f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #is free-running.
1dc0096f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc0096f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• Minor note*
1dc0096f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #`wstdmainit` configures an initial transfer count of `15` but that value is always
1dc00970 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #overridden before the channel starts in `vid_fieldi`, so it's harmless but slightly misleading.
1dc00970 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc00970 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The missing headers `pal576i.h` and `monobit.h` presumably define the frame buffers and word counts
1dc00970 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #— sharing those would complete the picture.
1dc00971 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
