1dc034b2 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #Yes, all good — just taking a proper look at these. Several things worth noting:
1dc034b2 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc034b3 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• fs.cpp*
1dc034b3 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The comment says "1MB" but `blockcount = 512` at 4KB blocks is actually 2MB. One of those needs
1dc034b3 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #correcting. Also `lfsformat` is called unconditionally in `lfs_test` — fine as a scratch test
1dc034b4 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #but would wipe existing data on every call in production use.
1dc034b4 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc034b4 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The read/write addressing split is correctly handled — reads use the XIP-mapped absolute address,
1dc034b4 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #writes and erases use the raw `FLASHTARGETOFFSET` as the SDK requires. That's easy to get
1dc034b5 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #wrong.
1dc034b5 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc034b5 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• Flash operations during video*
1dc034b5 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #`saveanddisable_interrupts` is used correctly, and since the video DMA feeds directly from
1dc034b6 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #RAM frame buffers into PIO, XIP suspension during flash writes won't disturb the signal. That's a
1dc034b6 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #fortunate consequence of the RAM-based frame buffer design.
1dc034b6 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc034b6 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• i2s.cpp*
1dc034b7 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The LFSR with a hold counter is a neat way to produce textured noise rather than pure white. The
1dc034b7 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #`0xdeadbeef` seed is fine. `fuzz` and `tick` as file-scope globals work here but would be worth
1dc034b7 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #encapsulating if the audio side grows.
1dc034b7 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc034b8 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• pal576i.cpp*
1dc034b8 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The equalizing and broad sync pulse structure looks correct for PAL 625-line interlaced, with the
1dc034b8 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #half-line `S0,S1` handoff between fields handled properly.
1dc034b8 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1dc034b9 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• monobit.cpp*
1dc034b9 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The `c64_rgb` array is defined but appears unused currently — presumably reserved for chroma work.
1dc034b9 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
