1ddc6f2d [claude-sonnet-4-6] #These are new to me — quite a substantial project. A few observations:
1ddc6f2d [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1ddc6f2d [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• PIO Design*
1ddc6f2e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The `out pindirs, 1` approach for pixel output is elegant — using pin direction to toggle between
1ddc6f2e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #driven-low (sync/black) and high-impedance (pulled high via resistor ladder = white) rather than
1ddc6f2e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #toggling the pin value itself. Clean way to get two video levels from one pin.
1ddc6f2e [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1ddc6f2f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• Resistor Network*
1ddc6f2f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The 120Ω/150Ω/75Ω network in the header comment is a tidy approach to composite mono. The chroma
1ddc6f2f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #additions (100Ω/330Ω) suggest colour work is in progress rather than complete.
1ddc6f2f [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1ddc6f30 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• WST Teletext*
1ddc6f30 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The Hamming 8/4 encoding and clock run-in (0x55, 0x55, 0x27) look correct for the standard. One
1ddc6f30 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #thing worth verifying is the byte timing relationship between the WST DMA and the video DMA —
1ddc6f30 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #teletext packets need to land in lines 7–22 precisely.
1ddc6f31 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1ddc6f31 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• Filesystem*
