1ddf09ec [deepseek-v4] #   - 384 × 16 = 6144 cycles
1ddf09ec [deepseek-v4] #   - Total = 957 + 6144 = 7101 cycles
1ddf09ec [deepseek-v4] #   - Ends at 2727 + 6144 = 8871 — within the active window.
1ddf09ed [deepseek-v4] #
1ddf09ed [deepseek-v4] #2. Correct the pixel timing to bring the line back to 10656 cycles. Change `out pindirs, 1
1ddf09ed [deepseek-v4] #[8]` to `[7]` (8 cycles per pixel plus 2 for the jmp = 10 cycles). Then:
1ddf09ee [deepseek-v4] #   - 864 × 10 = 8640 cycles → matches the comment
1ddf09ee [deepseek-v4] #   - Total line = 813 + 957 + 8640 + 265 ≈ 10675 (close enough; trim hsync or back porch by one
1ddf09ee [deepseek-v4] #iteration).
1ddf09ee [deepseek-v4] #
1ddf09ef [deepseek-v4] #3. Fix DMA channel — `wstdmainit` uses `&pio0->txf[sm]` but WST is now on `pio1`.
1ddf09ef [deepseek-v4] #Change to `&pio1->txf[sm]`.
