1e125d3e [gemini-3.1-pro] #PIO state machines to Video, Teletext (WST), Chroma, Audio, and Keyboard input, you are fully
1e125d3f [gemini-3.1-pro] #utilizing the RP2350's concurrent hardware capabilities. The main loop is kept lightweight,
1e125d3f [gemini-3.1-pro] #primarily handling DMA re-arming and state monitoring, which is ideal for maintaining strict video
1e125d3f [gemini-3.1-pro] #timings.
1e125d3f [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e125d3f [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Teletext (WST) Implementation*
1e125d40 [gemini-3.1-pro] #The software-side preparation of the World System Teletext packets is cleanly handled.
1e125d40 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Pre-calculating the Hamming 8/4 encoding via a lookup table and applying odd parity in software
1e125d40 [gemini-3.1-pro] #ensures the PIO machine only needs to focus on shifting the bits out at the correct frequency.
1e125d40 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Grouping the 48-byte packets into 12 32-bit words for the DMA transfer is an efficient use of the
1e125d41 [gemini-3.1-pro] #bus.
1e125d41 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e125d41 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Chroma Synthesis*
1e125d41 [gemini-3.1-pro] #The `initChroma` function demonstrates a clever approach to generating the color subcarrier. By
1e125d42 [gemini-3.1-pro] #pre-packing the 4-phase sine wave approximation (0, 1, 1, 0) into 32-bit arrays, you offload the
1e125d42 [gemini-3.1-pro] #high-speed signal generation entirely to the DMA and PIO. The inclusion of the color burst
1e125d42 [gemini-3.1-pro] #sequences (burst0 and burst1) at the start of the lines is handled seamlessly within the same data
