1e17ad29 [gemini-3.1-pro] #A Quick Note on YPbPr Analog Colors
1e17ad29 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e17ad29 [gemini-3.1-pro] #I see how you set up your test palette (e.g., `(6,6,6)`, `(3,3,3)`, `(0,0,0)`). This will
1e17ad29 [gemini-3.1-pro] #absolutely produce distinct colors on the screen, but when you are ready to tune them into exact
1e17ad2a [gemini-3.1-pro] #colors (like pure black, pure white, pure red), keep in mind how the Component Video
1e17ad2a [gemini-3.1-pro] #(YPbPr) color space works.
1e17ad2a [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e17ad2a [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Y (Luma/Brightness): This is your black-and-white image.
1e17ad2b [gemini-3.1-pro] #    *   `0` (High-Z) = Maximum Voltage = White
1e17ad2b [gemini-3.1-pro] #    *   `6` (Drive Low) = Minimum Voltage = Black
1e17ad2b [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Pb and Pr (Color Differences): These signals rest at a neutral center voltage
1e17ad2b [gemini-3.1-pro] #when there is no color (greyscale).
1e17ad2c [gemini-3.1-pro] #    *   `3` is your neutral point.
