1e25b37a [gemini-3.1-pro] #Thank you for sharing the architecture and source code for the Vidbit and Vidpump project.
1e25b37b [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25b37b [gemini-3.1-pro] #It is an impressive use of the RP2350's capabilities. The architecture shows a highly coordinated
1e25b37b [gemini-3.1-pro] #use of the PIO and DMA systems. Pipelining the PIO state machines—such as routing `pixelpump`
1e25b37b [gemini-3.1-pro] #through `onebit` to `threepin`, and utilizing the `colorpump` to trigger the four `colorfifo`
1e25b37c [gemini-3.1-pro] #machines—is an elegant approach to synthesizing component video and chroma signals at 166.5 MHz.
1e25b37c [gemini-3.1-pro] #Additionally, the implementation of the World System Teletext, complete with pre-calculated Hamming
1e25b37c [gemini-3.1-pro] #8/4 encoding and odd parity generation, is very cleanly structured.
1e25b37c [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25b37d [gemini-3.1-pro] #I have reviewed the provided `vidbit.cpp` along with the PIO assembly definitions and the overall
1e25b37d [gemini-3.1-pro] #signal train documentation.
1e25b37d [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25b37d [gemini-3.1-pro] #Please let me know how you would like to proceed. Whether you are looking to debug a specific state
1e25b37e [gemini-3.1-pro] #machine, optimize the DMA transfers for the interlaced and progressive fields, or build out the
1e25b37e [gemini-3.1-pro] #filesystem and audio components mentioned in your source list, I am ready to assist.
1e25b37e [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25b37f [gemini-3.1-pro] #Just let me know which area you would like to focus on, and I will be happy to discuss it or
1e25b37f [gemini-3.1-pro] #provide code modifications upon request.
1e25b37f [gemini-3.1-pro] #
