1e25ccc6 [gemini-3.1-pro] #pio_sm_exec(pio, sm, pio_encode_mov(pio_isr, pio_osr));
1e25ccc6 [gemini-3.1-pro] #pio_sm_exec(pio, sm, pio_encode_out(pio_null, 32)); // <--- ADD THIS to empty the OSR
1e25ccc6 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25ccc7 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25ccc7 [gemini-3.1-pro] #3. Read from the correct FIFO in `colorfifo.pio`
1e25ccc7 [gemini-3.1-pro] #In `vidbit.cpp`, you use `piosmput_blocking` to preload the 4 color trains. This function
1e25ccc7 [gemini-3.1-pro] #writes to the TX FIFO.
1e25ccc8 [gemini-3.1-pro] #However, in `colorfifo.pio`, your instruction is `mov osr, rxfifo[y]`. Because the RX FIFO is
1e25ccc8 [gemini-3.1-pro] #empty, it outputs all `0`s, resulting in no color.
1e25ccc8 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25ccc8 [gemini-3.1-pro] #The RP2350 allows you to index the TX FIFO directly. Update `colorfifo.pio` to read from `txfifo`:
1e25ccc9 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1e25ccc9 [gemini-3.1-pro] #stall:
