1e3b5356 [nitro@ryzen5] can i make sharedfiles an array of a particular type
1e3b538e [deepseek-v4] #Yes, you can declare `sharedfiles` as an array of a particular type. In TypeScript, you would use
1e3b538e [deepseek-v4] #either `Array<YourType>` or `YourType[]` syntax. For example:
1e3b538e [deepseek-v4] #
1e3b538e [deepseek-v4] #- `let sharedfiles: File[];` for an array of `File` objects.
1e3b538e [deepseek-v4] #- `let sharedfiles: Array<string>;` for an array of strings.
1e3b538f [deepseek-v4] #
1e3b538f [deepseek-v4] #In plain JavaScript, you can use JSDoc type annotations or rely on runtime checks, though static
1e3b538f [deepseek-v4] #typing is more robust. If you can tell me the specific type and language you're using, I can offer
