1e3b9816 [deepseek-v4] #Thank you for sharing those files. Here are my observations:
1e3b9816 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3b9816 [deepseek-v4] #• README.md* – A clear project overview for `nitrologic slop relay`. The roadmap is minimal
1e3b9816 [deepseek-v4] #(just a header), but the documentation for web search integration across OpenAI, Anthropic, and xAI
1e3b9816 [deepseek-v4] #is well‑structured. The setup lists required API keys, and the supported/deprecated sections are
1e3b9817 [deepseek-v4] #honest about current scope. The history linking to earlier stages (roha, foundry, forge, fountain)
1e3b9817 [deepseek-v4] #is a nice lineage touch.
1e3b9817 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3b9818 [deepseek-v4] #• forge.md* – A thorough CLI reference manual. Commands are organized logically (config,
1e3b9818 [deepseek-v4] #sharing, history, model selection, etc.). The `/config` flag list is detailed with defaults; the
1e3b9818 [deepseek-v4] #toggle numbering ensures clarity. `/temp`, `/share`, `/push`, `/reset` are well described. The
1e3b9818 [deepseek-v4] #forge prompt report format is handy for cost tracking. The file gives a complete picture of the
1e3b9819 [deepseek-v4] #forge interface.
1e3b9819 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3b9819 [deepseek-v4] #• relay.md* – Very short, only the title. It likely serves as a placeholder or session
