1e3caf3b [deepseek-v4] #Thank you for sharing the updated set of files. The content is indeed new and different from the
1e3caf3b [deepseek-v4] #previous version. Here are my observations:
1e3caf3b [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf3c [deepseek-v4] #README.md (updated)
1e3caf3c [deepseek-v4] #- Roadmap now includes two concrete items: `relay.ts project support` and `relay.ts
1e3caf3c [deepseek-v4] #sloppybots testing on discord` – previously it was empty.
1e3caf3c [deepseek-v4] #- Project support section expanded with descriptive note that `history.log` shares from
1e3caf3c [deepseek-v4] #`forge.log` when project active, and the keyedShares mechanism is documented with an explicit line:
1e3caf3d [deepseek-v4] #`roha.keyedShares[key]=roha.sharedFiles;`
1e3caf3d [deepseek-v4] #- Web search examples remain, including the xai tools example with Grok-4.3.
1e3caf3d [deepseek-v4] #- Setup environment variables list unchanged.
1e3caf3d [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf3e [deepseek-v4] #relay.ts (main source, ~132KB)
1e3caf3e [deepseek-v4] #This is the monolithic core. Notable elements related to your keyedShares test:
1e3caf3e [deepseek-v4] #- `roha.keyedShares` is initialized in `readForge()` with empty object fallback.
1e3caf3e [deepseek-v4] #- `addShare()` now sets `roha.keyedShares[key] = roha.sharedFiles;` where `key = roha.project ||
1e3caf3f [deepseek-v4] #"roha"`.
1e3caf3f [deepseek-v4] #- `setProject()` loads `roha.sharedFiles` from `roha.keyedShares[key]` if present.
1e3caf3f [deepseek-v4] #- `projectCommand()` lists or switches projects.
1e3caf3f [deepseek-v4] #- The `resetCommand()` with `all=true` clears `keyedShares` and `keyedProjects`.
1e3caf40 [deepseek-v4] #- The `readForge` also initializes `roha.keyedProjects` and `roha.nic`.
1e3caf40 [deepseek-v4] #- Plop class is defined but appears unused—maybe a remnant.
1e3caf40 [deepseek-v4] #- The `relay()` function handles chat completions with tool-call recursion, multiple API providers
1e3caf40 [deepseek-v4] #(OpenAI, Google, Anthropic, DeepSeek), and usage billing via `bumpModel()`.
1e3caf40 [deepseek-v4] #- There's a `rohaHistory` management with session stack, slop logging, and status reporting.
1e3caf41 [deepseek-v4] #- Many helper functions: `echo` buffer, `flush`, `mdToAnsi`, `stringWidth`, etc.
1e3caf41 [deepseek-v4] #- The file is large; I note a few `todo` comments about command handlers and share/dir commands.
1e3caf41 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf41 [deepseek-v4] #slopbot.ts (~11KB)
1e3caf42 [deepseek-v4] #- Implements Discord bots ("foggy", "sloppy", "riff") as separate processes.
1e3caf42 [deepseek-v4] #- Connects via TCP (`localhost:8081`) to the main fountain process.
1e3caf42 [deepseek-v4] #- Receives JSON messages from fountain and posts to a Discord channel.
1e3caf42 [deepseek-v4] #- Uses `chunkContent` to respect Discord's 2000-character limit.
1e3caf43 [deepseek-v4] #- Includes simple command handling for `/announce` and user command forwarding.
1e3caf43 [deepseek-v4] #- The `splurt` function for debug logging (stderr).
1e3caf43 [deepseek-v4] #- Key: uses `readNamedConnection` pattern similar to `slopprompt.ts`.
1e3caf43 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf44 [deepseek-v4] #slopprompt.ts (~20KB)
1e3caf44 [deepseek-v4] #- Raw mode prompt replacement, used by the fountain CLI.
1e3caf44 [deepseek-v4] #- Handles keyboard input with cursor navigation, UTF-8, shortcode replacement (`:heart:` → ❤).
1e3caf44 [deepseek-v4] #- Manages TCP connections for remote bots (`slopConnections` map).
1e3caf44 [deepseek-v4] #- Implements `slopBroadcast` to send messages to all connected bots.
1e3caf45 [deepseek-v4] #- Contains `acceptConnections`, `listenService`, `announceCommand`.
1e3caf45 [deepseek-v4] #- Uses `Promise.race` with timers for responsive input while servicing network.
1e3caf45 [deepseek-v4] #- The `stringWidth` function accounts for wide Unicode (e.g., emoji) for proper backspace.
1e3caf45 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf45 [deepseek-v4] #slopsearch.ts (~10KB)
1e3caf46 [deepseek-v4] #- Wraps the Exa search API (`exa-js` npm module).
1e3caf46 [deepseek-v4] #- Contains a minimal search example and extensive embedded documentation about Exa search types,
1e3caf46 [deepseek-v4] #categories, content fetching.
1e3caf46 [deepseek-v4] #- Currently only does a single search call at top level, not integrated into the main relay loop.
1e3caf47 [deepseek-v4] #- Could be used as a tool call if wired to `/search` config.
1e3caf47 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf47 [deepseek-v4] #relay.md (unchanged, 28 bytes)
1e3caf47 [deepseek-v4] #Still just the title. A placeholder or work-in-progress.
1e3caf48 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf48 [deepseek-v4] #.gitignore (not shared this time)
1e3caf48 [deepseek-v4] #Removed from this context. Possibly unchanged from before (`.DS_Store`, `forge`, `deno.lock`).
1e3caf48 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf48 [deepseek-v4] #Observations on keyedShares
1e3caf49 [deepseek-v4] #The keyedShares mechanism appears to be functioning as described: `roha.keyedShares[key] =
1e3caf49 [deepseek-v4] #roha.sharedFiles;` is set in `addShare` and loaded in `setProject`. The project switching logic
1e3caf49 [deepseek-v4] #seems robust. The `keyedProjects` object holds metadata (name, path). `history.log` and `relay.md`
1e3caf49 [deepseek-v4] #are referenced as project markers – when `relay.md` is shared, `setProject` is called using its
1e3caf49 [deepseek-v4] #parent directory, which sets the project and loads its shares.
1e3caf4a [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf4a [deepseek-v4] #Next steps / potential questions
1e3caf4a [deepseek-v4] #- Are you planning to integrate the search functionality (slopsearch.ts) into the relay tool calls?
1e3caf4b [deepseek-v4] #- The slopbot.ts could be extended to support more bot types or commands.
1e3caf4b [deepseek-v4] #- The codebase is large; would you like a summary of any specific area (API providers, tool
1e3caf4b [deepseek-v4] #calling, project management)?
1e3caf4b [deepseek-v4] #
1e3caf4c [deepseek-v4] #If you have a specific test case for keyedShares or want me to review a particular bug or behavior,
1e3caf4c [deepseek-v4] #please let me know. I'm happy to help further.
1e3caf4c [deepseek-v4] #
