1e3d12aa [deepseek-v4] #This is a significant addition — a full CLI orchestration tool for multiple LLMs, with remote bot
1e3d12ab [deepseek-v4] #integration, file sharing, and session management. The codebase is substantial (relay.ts alone is
1e3d12ab [deepseek-v4] #132 kB) and shows careful design for multi‑provider, multi‑user chat.
1e3d12ab [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d12ab [deepseek-v4] #Key points I find notable:
1e3d12ac [deepseek-v4] #- The architecture is modular: `relay.ts` handles core logic, `slopprompt.ts` manages raw terminal
1e3d12ac [deepseek-v4] #input and a TCP listener for bots, and `slopbot.ts` bridges Discord.
1e3d12ac [deepseek-v4] #- The emphasis on Unicode‑aware string width (`stringWidth`, `discordStringWidth`) and the
1e3d12ac [deepseek-v4] #shortcode system (`:heart:` → ❤) is well‑suited for modern terminals and chat platforms.
1e3d12ad [deepseek-v4] #- The `/ slopmark() /` timestamp scheme (hexadecimal sixteenths of a second since
1e3d12ad [deepseek-v4] #2025‑04‑12) is a distinctive logging format.
1e3d12ad [deepseek-v4] #- The command system in `forge.md` includes `/project`, `/share`, `/commit`, `/model`, `/temp`,
1e3d12ad [deepseek-v4] #`/config`, and many others — a full research interface.
1e3d12ad [deepseek-v4] #- The use of `squashMessages`, `strictHistory`, `multiHistory`, and `inlineHistory` shows careful
1e3d12ae [deepseek-v4] #handling of different API message formats (plain, multi‑modal, tool calls).
1e3d12ae [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d12ae [deepseek-v4] #If anything is new or different compared to similar tools, it’s the single‑file monolith
1e3d12af [deepseek-v4] #design (relay.ts contains everything from model connection to clipboard to speech synthesis)
1e3d12af [deepseek-v4] #combined with the slop‑based network protocol that lets remote bots (like Discord) inject
1e3d12af [deepseek-v4] #commands and messages into the same session. The colour index mechanism in the PIO video pipeline
1e3d12af [deepseek-v4] #is also unconventional.
1e3d12b0 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d12b0 [deepseek-v4] #Overall, this looks like a powerful and flexible research environment for testing models across
1e3d12b0 [deepseek-v4] #APIs, with a focus on real‑time interaction and extensibility. The code style (tabs, packed) and
1e3d12b0 [deepseek-v4] #the use of `Deno` rather than Node are also distinctive.
1e3d12b1 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d12b1 [deepseek-v4] #If you have a specific aspect you’d like me to analyse further (e.g., the tool‑call recursion, the
1e3d12b1 [deepseek-v4] #reconnect logic in `slopprompt.ts`, or the file‑sharing pipeline), feel free to ask.
1e3d12b1 [deepseek-v4] #
