1e3d149b [deepseek-v4] #Noted. The `/project` command implementation in `relay.ts` and its documentation in `forge.md` now
1e3d149b [deepseek-v4] #appear to include support for keyed projects (`roha.keyedProjects`) and keyed
1e3d149b [deepseek-v4] #shares (`roha.keyedShares`), along with automatic history log detection and directory
1e3d149b [deepseek-v4] #switching. The addition of `listProjects`, `setProject`, and `loadProject` functions suggests more
1e3d149b [deepseek-v4] #robust project management.
1e3d149b [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d149c [deepseek-v4] #Specifically, the new behaviour:
1e3d149c [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d149c [deepseek-v4] #- The `/project` command (without arguments) lists all known project keys and their associated
1e3d149c [deepseek-v4] #shares.
1e3d149d [deepseek-v4] #- `setProject(name, path)` records the project path, sets `roha.project`, changes the working
1e3d149d [deepseek-v4] #directory to that path, and loads any previously shared files from `keyedShares`.
1e3d149d [deepseek-v4] #- `loadProject(name)` looks up the project by key and calls `setProject` internally.
1e3d149d [deepseek-v4] #- Automatic project detection when sharing a `relay.md` file: the directory name becomes the
1e3d149e [deepseek-v4] #project key.
1e3d149e [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d149e [deepseek-v4] #This is a clean way to isolate contexts between different codebases or research threads without
1e3d149f [deepseek-v4] #manual history resets. The integration with `forge.log` and `history.log` within each project
1e3d149f [deepseek-v4] #directory also means logging and continuation are seamless.
1e3d149f [deepseek-v4] #
1e3d149f [deepseek-v4] #If you have specific notes or annotations added to this command (e.g., user‑facing help text or
1e3d14a0 [deepseek-v4] #inline documentation), feel free to share them for review. Otherwise, the current design looks
1e3d14a0 [deepseek-v4] #solid.
1e3d14a0 [deepseek-v4] #
