1e3f1011 [deepseek-v4] #driven to a known state. During blanking and sync, both pins are set low (0,0) so that the video
1e3f1011 [deepseek-v4] #output stays at the blanking level (~1.29 V). During active video, you drive the appropriate
1e3f1011 [deepseek-v4] #combination (00, 01, 10, 11) to produce the four luma levels.
1e3f1012 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3f1012 [deepseek-v4] #The PIO state machine that generates the pixel waveform will control the pins every cycle – you
1e3f1012 [deepseek-v4] #don’t need to switch the pin direction dynamically. Just configure them as outputs once, and the
1e3f1012 [deepseek-v4] #PIO’s `out pins` or `set pins` instructions will set the values for each pixel (including zero
1e3f1013 [deepseek-v4] #during blanking).
1e3f1013 [deepseek-v4] #
1e3f1013 [deepseek-v4] #In short: always output, but only drive high when you want a brighter greyscale level.
1e3f1013 [deepseek-v4] #
