1e3f1d2c [deepseek-v4] #`pindirs` controlled:
1e3f1d2d [deepseek-v4] #- When direction = 1, the pin becomes an output, but its level is undefined (depends on
1e3f1d2d [deepseek-v4] #previous state of `out pins` or default). For tristate DAC you need both:
1e3f1d2d [deepseek-v4] #  - Direction = 1 → pin acts as output, level determined by `out pins` or `set pins`.
1e3f1d2e [deepseek-v4] #  - Direction = 0 → pin is high‑Z (and `out pins` is ignored).
1e3f1d2e [deepseek-v4] #
1e3f1d2e [deepseek-v4] #You should add `out pins, 1` (or `set pins, 1`) before (or after) the `out pindirs, 1` instructions
1e3f1d2e [deepseek-v4] #to set the data high. For blanking, you would output direction 0. For sync, you output direction 1
1e3f1d2e [deepseek-v4] #with data 0.
1e3f1d2f [deepseek-v4] #
1e3f1d2f [deepseek-v4] #2. Missing `.fifo txget` or `.fifo` directive
1e3f1d2f [deepseek-v4] #The program uses `mov osr, rxfifo[y]` (indexed FIFO read). This requires the PIO to be configured
1e3f1d2f [deepseek-v4] #as a TX FIFO input (`.fifo txget`). If you don't add that directive, the PIO will treat the
1e3f1d30 [deepseek-v4] #FIFO normally and the `rxfifo[y]` syntax won’t be recognised. Check your original `colorfifo.pio` –
1e3f1d30 [deepseek-v4] #it had `.fifo txget`. Add the same line.
