1e534e02 [claude-sonnet-4-6] # ꔀ nitrologic Relay 1.8.5 ⛲  claude-sonnet-4-6 A\ 🪠 🧊 $0.129 74.45KB 72.87s
1e534e02 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #Several things stand out as new or evolved from earlier versions:
1e534e03 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1e534e03 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• greyline.pio* appears to be a new addition — it mirrors the `rxfifo[y]` lookup approach
1e534e03 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #from colorfifo but drives a single grey pin using preloaded PDM pulse trains. The `greyinit` in
1e534e03 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #vidbit.cpp preloads indices 0,2,4,6 from `pdmpatterns`, giving four clean levels: 0/6, 2/6,
1e534e04 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #4/6, 6/6 — black through white.
1e534e04 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1e534e04 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• vidbit.pio* now fires two IRQs in the active region — `irq set 5` at line start
1e534e04 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #(targeting colorpump) and `irq set 6 [6]` per pixel (targeting greyline). The 6-cycle hold on IRQ 6
1e534e05 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #gives greyline enough headroom to complete its wait/mov/mov/6×pindirs sequence within the pixel
1e534e05 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #window.
1e534e05 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1e534e05 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• colorpump.pio* has grown substantially from the .md sketch — it now has the IRQ 5 wait, a
1e534e06 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #`mov y, isr` pixel counter, and the timing-equalising done1/done2/done3 nop chain to keep all four
1e534e06 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #index paths at equal cycle cost.
1e534e06 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1e534e06 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #• threepin.pio* differs from the vidpump.md documentation — it has 7 `out pindirs` per
1e534e07 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #pixel (not 10), discarding 11 bits to complete a 32-bit word (3×7+11=32), while the .md version
1e534e07 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #described 10 pindirs with a 2-bit skip.
1e534e07 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
1e534e07 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #The current build in vidbit.cpp has `GREY` and `LACE` active, with `COLOR`, `WST` and `CHROMA`
1e534e08 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #compiled out.
1e534e08 [claude-sonnet-4-6] #
