1e53aa50 [claude-haiku-4-5] # ꔀ nitrologic Relay 1.8.5 ⛲  claude-haiku-4-5 A\ 🪠 🧊 $0.027 74.54KB 20.46s
1e53aa50 [claude-haiku-4-5] #VIDBIT Analysis
1e53aa50 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa50 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Reviewing the shared files for the RP2350 PAL video system. Notable observations:
1e53aa51 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa51 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Architecture Overview
1e53aa51 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa51 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• System Clock:* 166.5 MHz, PAL 576i interlaced video (625 lines @ 25Hz)
1e53aa52 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Line Timing:* 64µs per line = 10,656 cycles @ 166.5MHz = 10 cycles/pixel
1e53aa52 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa52 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• PIO State Machines:*
1e53aa52 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- SM0: `vidbit.pio` - Main PAL sync/video waveform
1e53aa53 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- SM1: `greyline.pio` - Greyscale luma output (GP18)
1e53aa53 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- SM1: `chroma.pio` - PAL color burst (2-pin DAC)
1e53aa53 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- SM2: `wst.pio` - World System Teletext data insertion
1e53aa53 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- SM2: `i2s.pio` - Audio I2S interface (48kHz stereo)
1e53aa54 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- SM3: `ps2.pio` - PS/2 keyboard input
1e53aa54 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa54 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Interesting Design Patterns
1e53aa54 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa55 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 1. Dual-field Interlace*
1e53aa55 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- `evenFrame[]` and `oddFrame[]` arrays (309/310 lines respectively)
1e53aa55 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- DMA switches frames per field via `vid_fieldi()`
1e53aa55 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Timing constants pre-calculated (E0/E1 for equalizing, B0/B1 for broad sync, S0/S1 for half-line)
1e53aa56 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa56 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 2. Color Subsystem* (commented but structured)
1e53aa56 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- `colorfifo.pio` - RxFIFO indexed by GP46/47 (2-bit color select)
1e53aa56 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- `colorpump.pio` - Demux 2-bit index into 4 side-set pulse trains
1e53aa57 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Pre-loaded 3-channel pulse trains in `color_trains[]`
1e53aa57 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa57 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 3. Greyscale PDM*
1e53aa57 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- `greyline.pio` uses indexed RxFIFO lookup: `mov osr, rxfifo[y]`
1e53aa58 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- 6-bit dither patterns in `pdm_patterns[7]`
1e53aa58 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Waits on IRQ6 per pixel cycle for timing sync
1e53aa58 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa58 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 4. Teletext Pipeline*
1e53aa59 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Hamming(8,4) encoding with odd parity
1e53aa59 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Header packets (mag/page/control) + body packets (40 chars)
1e53aa59 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Lines 7-22 insertion per field
1e53aa59 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa5a [claude-haiku-4-5] #Questions/Observations
1e53aa5a [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa5a [claude-haiku-4-5] #1. `colorfifo.pio` syntax - Is `rxfifo[y]` valid PIO assembly? I haven't seen indexed FIFO
1e53aa5a [claude-haiku-4-5] #reads in standard RP2040 PIO. Is this RP2350-specific?
1e53aa5b [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53aa5b [claude-haiku-4-5] #2. Clkdiv Precision - `smconfigset_clkdiv(pio, sm, 2.3471f)` for chroma - is this
1e53aa5b [claude-haiku-4-5] #calibrated for PAL subcarrier (4.43361875 MHz)? Math checks: 166.5MHz / 2.3471 ≈ 70.9 MHz (seems
