1e53d40f [claude-haiku-4-5] #RP2350 PIO Programming Guide
1e53d40f [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d40f [claude-haiku-4-5] #Chapter 11: PIO (Programmable Input/Output)
1e53d40f [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d410 [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.1 Overview
1e53d410 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d410 [claude-haiku-4-5] #RP2350 contains 3 identical PIO blocks. Each PIO block has:
1e53d410 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- 4 state machines
1e53d411 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Dedicated connections to bus fabric, GPIO, and interrupt controller
1e53d411 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Shared 32-instruction memory (all 4 SMs read from same memory)
1e53d411 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d411 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Each state machine includes:*
1e53d411 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Two 32-bit shift registers (ISR, OSR)
1e53d412 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Two 32-bit scratch registers (X, Y)
1e53d412 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- 4 × 32-bit TX/RX FIFOs (reconfigurable as 8×32 single direction)
1e53d412 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Fractional clock divider (16-bit integer + 8-bit fractional)
1e53d412 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Flexible GPIO mapping
1e53d413 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- DMA interface (up to 1 word/clock throughput)
1e53d413 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- 8 IRQ flags (shareable across PIO blocks)
1e53d413 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d413 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Silicon efficiency:* Each SM occupies roughly the same area as a standard serial
1e53d414 [claude-haiku-4-5] #interface (SPI/I2C), but provides vastly more flexibility.
1e53d414 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d414 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Performance:* Can sustain 360 Mb/s (DPI output @ 48 MHz system clock).
1e53d414 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d415 [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d415 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d415 [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.1.1 Changes from RP2040 → RP2350
1e53d415 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d416 [claude-haiku-4-5] #╭───────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────╮
1e53d416 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  Feature                  │  RP2350                   │  Use Case                                  │
1e53d416 [claude-haiku-4-5] #├───────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
1e53d416 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **Version field**        │  DBG_CFGINFO.VERSION = 1  │  Runtime feature detection                 │
1e53d417 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **GPIO base**            │  GPIOBASE register        │  Support >32 GPIOs per block               │
1e53d417 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **Cross-PIO sync**       │  CTRL.NEXT/PREV_PIO_MASK  │  Sync state machines across blocks         │
1e53d417 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **Input masking**        │  SM0_SHIFTCTRL.IN_COUNT   │  MOV x, PINS returns only needed bits      │
1e53d417 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **All 8 IRQs exposed**   │  IRQ0_INTE, IRQ1_INTE     │  System-level interrupts from all flags    │
1e53d418 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **Indexed RX FIFO GET**  │  `mov osr, rxfifo[y]`     │  Random-access lookup tables (v1 only)     │
1e53d418 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **Indexed RX FIFO PUT**  │  `mov rxfifo[y], isr`     │  Random-access status registers (v1 only)  │
1e53d418 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **PINDIRS in MOV**       │  `mov pindirs, x`         │  Bulk pin direction control                │
1e53d418 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **MOV STATUS**           │  SM IRQ flags as source   │  Conditional jumps on IRQ state            │
1e53d419 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **Cross-PIO IRQ**        │  `irq next/prev set n`    │  IRQ coordination across PIO blocks        │
1e53d419 [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  **WAIT JMPPIN offset**   │  `wait 1 jmppin +2`       │  Flexible branch pin selection             │
1e53d419 [claude-haiku-4-5] #╰───────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────╯
1e53d419 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41a [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d41a [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41a [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.2 Programmer's Model
1e53d41a [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41b [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.2.1 PIO Programs
1e53d41b [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41b [claude-haiku-4-5] #- 9 instructions total: JMP, WAIT, IN, OUT, PUSH, PULL, MOV, IRQ, SET
1e53d41b [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Assembly format: `.pio` text files → compiled by `pioasm` → C header constants
1e53d41c [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Execution: 1 instruction per clock (unless stalled)
1e53d41c [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Delays: 0-31 cycle inserts before next instruction
1e53d41c [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41c [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Example: Square wave*
1e53d41d [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41d [claude-haiku-4-5] #.program squarewave
1e53d41d [claude-haiku-4-5] #set pindirs, 1      ; Set pin to output
1e53d41d [claude-haiku-4-5] #again:
1e53d41e [claude-haiku-4-5] #    set pins, 1 [1] ; Drive high, delay 1 cycle
1e53d41e [claude-haiku-4-5] #    set pins, 0     ; Drive low
1e53d41e [claude-haiku-4-5] #    jmp again       ; Loop
1e53d41e [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41f [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41f [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d41f [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d41f [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.2.2 Control Flow
1e53d420 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d420 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Program Counter (PC):*
1e53d420 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Increments by 1 each cycle (wraps at end of memory)
1e53d420 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- JMP instructions set PC explicitly
1e53d421 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- WAIT stalls without advancing PC
1e53d421 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Side-set executes even during stall
1e53d421 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d421 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Clock divider:* Scales state machine speed by fractional factor (1 to 65536).
1e53d422 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d422 [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d422 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d422 [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.2.3 Registers
1e53d423 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d423 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Output Shift Register (OSR)
1e53d423 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d423 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Holds data flowing from TX FIFO → pins/destinations.
1e53d424 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d424 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- PULL: Load 32-bit word from TX FIFO → OSR
1e53d424 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- OUT: Shift 1…32 bits from OSR → destination
1e53d424 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Autopull: Hardware auto-refills OSR when shift threshold reached
1e53d425 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Shift direction: Configurable left/right
1e53d425 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d425 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Example:* Stream bytes at 1 byte per 2 clocks:
1e53d425 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d426 [claude-haiku-4-5] #.program pull_example
1e53d426 [claude-haiku-4-5] #loop:
1e53d426 [claude-haiku-4-5] #    out pins, 8
1e53d426 [claude-haiku-4-5] #pull
1e53d427 [claude-haiku-4-5] #    out pins, 8 [1]
1e53d427 [claude-haiku-4-5] #    out pins, 8 [1]
1e53d427 [claude-haiku-4-5] #    out pins, 8
1e53d427 [claude-haiku-4-5] #    jmp loop
1e53d428 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d428 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d428 [claude-haiku-4-5] #With autopull enabled, simplifies to:
1e53d428 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d429 [claude-haiku-4-5] #.program autopull_example
1e53d429 [claude-haiku-4-5] #.wrap_target
1e53d429 [claude-haiku-4-5] #    out pins, 8 [1]
1e53d429 [claude-haiku-4-5] #.wrap
1e53d42a [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42a [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42a [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d42a [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42a [claude-haiku-4-5] #Input Shift Register (ISR)
1e53d42b [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42b [claude-haiku-4-5] #Holds data flowing from pins/sources → RX FIFO.
1e53d42b [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42b [claude-haiku-4-5] #- IN: Shift 1…32 bits from source → ISR
1e53d42c [claude-haiku-4-5] #- PUSH: Write ISR contents to RX FIFO (clears ISR to 0)
1e53d42c [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Autopush: Hardware auto-pushes when shift threshold reached
1e53d42c [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Shift direction: Configurable left/right
1e53d42c [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42d [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Use:* Pad with zeroes after serial input:
1e53d42d [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42d [claude-haiku-4-5] #in pins, 8      ; Shift in 8 data bits (LSB first)
1e53d42d [claude-haiku-4-5] #in null, 24     ; Shift in 24 zero bits for alignment
1e53d42e [claude-haiku-4-5] #push            ; Push to RX FIFO
1e53d42e [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42e [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42e [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d42f [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42f [claude-haiku-4-5] #Scratch Registers (X, Y)
1e53d42f [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d42f [claude-haiku-4-5] #- 32-bit general purpose
1e53d430 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Loop counters: `set x, 15; ... jmp x-- loop`
1e53d430 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Conditional branching: `jmp !x skip` (branch if X=0)
1e53d430 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Temporary storage: Save/restore via MOV
1e53d430 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d431 [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d431 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d431 [claude-haiku-4-5] #FIFOs
1e53d431 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d432 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Each SM has:
1e53d432 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- TX FIFO (4 entries): System → SM (for data output)
1e53d432 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- RX FIFO (4 entries): SM → system (for data input)
1e53d432 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- DREQ signals: Drive DMA on FIFO activity
1e53d433 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- FJOIN option: Merge into 8-entry single-direction FIFO
1e53d433 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d433 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• New modes (RP2350):*
1e53d433 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- FJOINRXGET: RX FIFO as indexed read-only storage
1e53d434 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- FJOINRXPUT: RX FIFO as indexed write-only status
1e53d434 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- FJOINRXPUTGET: Both (system access disabled)
1e53d434 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d434 [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d435 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d435 [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.2.4 Stalling
1e53d435 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d435 [claude-haiku-4-5] #State machine pauses when:
1e53d436 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- WAIT condition not met
1e53d436 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- PULL from empty TX FIFO (blocking)
1e53d436 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- PUSH to full RX FIFO (blocking)
1e53d436 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- OUT with autopull, OSR exhausted, TX FIFO empty
1e53d437 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- IN with autopush, ISR full, RX FIFO full
1e53d437 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- IRQ WAIT on set flag, waiting for clear
1e53d437 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d437 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Side-set exception:* Always executes, even during stall.
1e53d438 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d438 [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d438 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d438 [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.2.5 Pin Mapping
1e53d439 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d439 [claude-haiku-4-5] #PIO controls 30 GPIOs (RP2350) with 4 independent pin groups:
1e53d439 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d439 [claude-haiku-4-5] #╭───────────────┬─────────────────┬───────────────────────────────╮
1e53d43a [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  Instruction  │  Pins Used      │  Config                       │
1e53d43a [claude-haiku-4-5] #├───────────────┼─────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┤
1e53d43a [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  OUT PINS     │  OUT pins       │  OUT_BASE, OUT_COUNT          │
1e53d43a [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  SET PINS     │  SET pins       │  SET_BASE, SET_COUNT          │
1e53d43b [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  Side-set     │  Side-set pins  │  SIDESET_BASE, SIDESET_COUNT  │
1e53d43b [claude-haiku-4-5] #│  IN PINS      │  IN pins        │  IN_BASE, IN_COUNT            │
1e53d43b [claude-haiku-4-5] #╰───────────────┴─────────────────┴───────────────────────────────╯
1e53d43b [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d43c [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Priority:* Highest-numbered SM wins on GPIO conflicts. Side-set overrides OUT/SET.
1e53d43c [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d43c [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e53d43c [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d43d [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.2.6 IRQ Flags
1e53d43d [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d43d [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 8 total flags* (0-7), visible to all SMs.
1e53d43d [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d43e [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Set/clear: IRQ instruction
1e53d43e [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Wait: WAIT IRQ instruction
