1e53d4a2 [claude-haiku-4-5] #11.5.6 GPIO Mapping
1e53d4a2 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d4a2 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Independent ranges for:*
1e53d4a2 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- OUT (PINS destination)
1e53d4a2 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- SET (PINS destination)
1e53d4a3 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Side-set
1e53d4a3 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- IN (PINS source)
1e53d4a3 [claude-haiku-4-5] #- JMP pin (independent)
1e53d4a3 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d4a4 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Each range:* `base + count` (wraps after GPIO 31).
1e53d4a4 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d4a4 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Priority:* Highest-numbered SM wins on conflicts.
1e53d4a4 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d4a5 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Input synchronisers:* 2-flipflop delay (protects metastability).
1e53d4a5 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e53d4a5 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Bypass:* `INPUTSYNCBYPASS` per GPIO (for synchronous interfaces).
