1e544dcb [claude-haiku-4-5] #Critical Observations
1e544dcb [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dcc [claude-haiku-4-5] #1. PIO Clock Divider Configuration (chroma.pio)
1e544dcc [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dcc [claude-haiku-4-5] #; Claims: clkdiv=9.3885 (PIO @ 17.734475MHz = 4x f_sc)
1e544dcc [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dcc [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Issue:* The comment states target frequency but the actual divider in C code:
1e544dcd [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dcd [claude-haiku-4-5] #pio_sm_set_clkdiv(pio,sm,2.3471f);  // chroma.pio line
1e544dcd [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dcd [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 9.3885 ≠ 2.3471* — these are inconsistent. If 166.5 MHz system clock, the math should be:
1e544dce [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Target: 4 × 4.43361875 MHz (PAL subcarrier × 4) = 17.734475 MHz
1e544dce [claude-haiku-4-5] #- Divisor: 166.5 / 17.734475 ≈ 9.388
1e544dce [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dce [claude-haiku-4-5] #The `2.3471` appears to be 166.5 / 71, which doesn't match PAL specs. Verify against actual
1e544dcf [claude-haiku-4-5] #output.
1e544dcf [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dcf [claude-haiku-4-5] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1e544dcf [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dd0 [claude-haiku-4-5] #2. Frame Buffer Layout Fragmentation (monobit.cpp)
1e544dd0 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e544dd0 [claude-haiku-4-5] #const int progressivePreamble=35;
1e544dd0 [claude-haiku-4-5] #const int progressiveLines=304;
