1e79ef45 [claude-haiku-4-5] #For Pico USB devices with CDC (Communications Device Class) support on Windows:
1e79ef45 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef45 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 1. SetupAPI + Device Interface GUID*
1e79ef45 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Query `GUIDDEVINTERFACECOMPORT` to enumerate CDC virtual COM ports. Most direct approach
1e79ef46 [claude-haiku-4-5] #for CDC devices.
1e79ef46 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef46 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 2. WMI Query*
1e79ef46 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Query `Win32SerialPort` filtered by `PNPDeviceID` containing "VID2E8A" (Raspberry Pi vendor
1e79ef47 [claude-haiku-4-5] #ID) and "PID_000A" (Pico CDC).
1e79ef47 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef47 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 3. Registry SERIALCOMM*
1e79ef47 [claude-haiku-4-5] #`HKEYLOCALMACHINE\HARDWARE\DEVICEMAP\SERIALCOMM` lists active COM ports. Can
1e79ef48 [claude-haiku-4-5] #cross-reference with USB device tree.
1e79ef48 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef48 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 4. libusb/libusbK*
1e79ef48 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Direct USB enumeration bypassing Windows CDC abstraction. Useful if you need raw USB control or
1e79ef49 [claude-haiku-4-5] #multiple Picos.
1e79ef49 [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef49 [claude-haiku-4-5] #• 5. EnumPorts API (Deprecated)*
1e79ef49 [claude-haiku-4-5] #Older but simpler; lists printer/serial ports though less detailed.
1e79ef4a [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef4a [claude-haiku-4-5] #• Best for Pico CDC detection:*
1e79ef4a [claude-haiku-4-5] #• SetupAPI with `GUIDDEVINTERFACECOMPORT`* - finds the virtual COM port, can
1e79ef4a [claude-haiku-4-5] #extract USB device info, reliable for hotplug detection.
1e79ef4b [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef4b [claude-haiku-4-5] #Alternatively, combining Registry SERIALCOMM with WMI device lookup gives you both
1e79ef4b [claude-haiku-4-5] #port names and USB identifiers without external dependencies.
1e79ef4b [claude-haiku-4-5] #
1e79ef4c [claude-haiku-4-5] #What's your intended use - just discovery, or also port management/communication?
1e79ef4c [claude-haiku-4-5] #
