1e7d25f4 [deepseek-v4] # ꔀ nitrologic Relay 1.8.6 ⛲  deepseek-v4 🐋 🪠 0.7° $0.112 1.194MB 69.44s
1e7d25f4 [deepseek-v4] #Thank you for sharing these files from the `pico-examples/pio` directory. They represent a standard
1e7d25f5 [deepseek-v4] #collection of Raspberry Pi Pico PIO (Programmable I/O) example projects, each demonstrating how to
1e7d25f5 [deepseek-v4] #implement various protocols and peripherals using PIO state machines.
1e7d25f5 [deepseek-v4] #
1e7d25f5 [deepseek-v4] #The examples cover a wide range of applications:
1e7d25f6 [deepseek-v4] #
1e7d25f6 [deepseek-v4] #- Basic I/O: `hellopio`, `pioblink`, `squarewave` – simple output and timing.
1e7d25f6 [deepseek-v4] #- Serial communication: `uarttx`, `uartrx`, `uart_dma` – software UART with
1e7d25f6 [deepseek-v4] #optional DMA and interrupt support.
1e7d25f7 [deepseek-v4] #- SPI: `spi` – full‑duplex SPI with multiple CPHA/CPOL modes and optional chip select.
1e7d25f7 [deepseek-v4] #- I2C: `i2c` – a PIO‑based I2C implementation with start/stop/repstart handling, bus
1e7d25f7 [deepseek-v4] #scanning, and blocking read/write.
1e7d25f7 [deepseek-v4] #- LED strips: `ws2812` and `ws2812_parallel` – driving WS2812 (NeoPixel) LEDs with
1e7d25f7 [deepseek-v4] #bit‑banged timing, including a parallel version.
1e7d25f8 [deepseek-v4] #- Display: `st7789_lcd` – driving an ST7789 colour LCD via a simple serial interface.
1e7d25f8 [deepseek-v4] #- PWM and encoders: `pwm`, `quadratureencoder`, `quadratureencoder_substep` – PWM
1e7d25f8 [deepseek-v4] #generation and quadrature decoding with sub‑step interpolation.
1e7d25f8 [deepseek-v4] #- Manchester encoding: `manchesterencoding`, `differentialmanchester` –
1e7d25f9 [deepseek-v4] #encoding/decoding Manchester and differential Manchester signals.
1e7d25f9 [deepseek-v4] #- Clock‑synchronous input: `clocked_input` – reading serial data with an external clock.
1e7d25f9 [deepseek-v4] #- Logic analyser: `logic_analyser` – using PIO with DMA to capture pin states at high
1e7d25f9 [deepseek-v4] #speed.
1e7d25fa [deepseek-v4] #- Miscellaneous: `addition` (PIO arithmetic), `apa102` (APA102 LED driver), `hub75` (RGB
1e7d25fa [deepseek-v4] #matrix panel), `onewire`, `ir_nec`.
1e7d25fa [deepseek-v4] #
1e7d25fa [deepseek-v4] #Each subdirectory contains `.c` source, `.pio` assembly, `CMakeLists.txt`, and often a header or
1e7d25fb [deepseek-v4] #readme. These are well‑known examples from the official Raspberry Pi Pico SDK and serve as a
1e7d25fb [deepseek-v4] #reference for implementing custom PIO‑based peripherals.
1e7d25fb [deepseek-v4] #
1e7d25fb [deepseek-v4] #If you have a specific question about any of these examples—such as how to adapt them to a
1e7d25fc [deepseek-v4] #different pinout, modify timing constants, or combine multiple PIO programs—I’d be happy to help.
1e7d25fc [deepseek-v4] #Otherwise, please let me know if you’re looking for something new or different in particular.
1e7d25fc [deepseek-v4] #
