1e96291a [kimi-k2.6] #
1e96291a [kimi-k2.6] #In PIO terms this means:
1e96291a [kimi-k2.6] #
1e96291a [kimi-k2.6] #1. 2-bit control field — The line preamble now shifts a 2-bit value from the FIFO into `Y`
1e96291b [kimi-k2.6] #to decide whether to fire the IRQ. On non-zero, it asserts flag 6 in the neighbouring PIO block.
1e96291b [kimi-k2.6] #2. Active IRQ — The handshake to PIO1 (chroma/colour/whatever is sitting on the other
1e96291b [kimi-k2.6] #block) is no longer dead code; it fires on lines where the control field is non-zero.
1e96291b [kimi-k2.6] #3. Serial pixel output — Most importantly, `set pins, 4` (which held the output at a
1e96291c [kimi-k2.6] #constant DC level) has been replaced by `out pins, 1`, so the state machine is now shifting actual
1e96291c [kimi-k2.6] #pixel data from the FIFO through the OSR to the pin during active video. Vidbit has gone from being
1e96291c [kimi-k2.6] #a sync-only generator to a sync-plus-luma bit-pump.
1e96291c [kimi-k2.6] #
