1e96372c [kimi-k2.6] #6` is re-executed after every pixel. Because `wait 1 irq` clears the flag when it succeeds,
1e96372c [kimi-k2.6] #the SM will stall immediately after its first pixel and sleep until the next line.
1e96372c [kimi-k2.6] #   If you want the IRQ to act as a line-start gate only, add `.wrap_target` before the
1e96372d [kimi-k2.6] #`mov` pair:
