1e963730 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e963730 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e963730 [kimi-k2.6] #   With that change the SM idles in blanking, then free-runs at 10 cycles/pixel for the whole
1e963730 [kimi-k2.6] #active period.
1e963730 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e963730 [kimi-k2.6] #2. Palette size
1e963731 [kimi-k2.6] #   `.fifo txget` exposes only four RX FIFO entries per state machine, so this SM gives you a
1e963731 [kimi-k2.6] #4-colour palette. The 16-entry `colortrains[]` array in `vidbit.cpp` implies you may
1e963731 [kimi-k2.6] #still want 16 colours. To get there you would need either four `colortrain` instances (each with a
1e963731 [kimi-k2.6] #different quadrant of the palette) or runtime reloading of the four `RXFxPUTGETy` registers
1e963731 [kimi-k2.6] #before each line.
1e963732 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e963732 [kimi-k2.6] #• Connection to the rest of the pipeline*
1e963732 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e963732 [kimi-k2.6] #- `vidbit.pio` (PIO0) still generates sync, burst gate and the luma bitstream.
1e963733 [kimi-k2.6] #- `colortrain.pio` (PIO1, SM1) waits on the cross-PIO flag, samples an index from its input pins,
1e963733 [kimi-k2.6] #and outputs the 3-pin chroma pulse train.
1e963733 [kimi-k2.6] #- The CPU renders a 2-bit-per-pixel framebuffer (`bitsPerPixel = 2` in `monobit.h`), but
1e963733 [kimi-k2.6] #`vidbit.pio` currently consumes both bits for luma (direction + level). If the colour index for
1e963733 [kimi-k2.6] #`colortrain` is meant to come from those same two bits, you will need to route one of them to the
1e963734 [kimi-k2.6] #SM’s input pin mapping or change the bit packing so that one bit drives luma and the other drives
1e963734 [kimi-k2.6] #chroma selection.
1e963734 [kimi-k2.6] #
