1e968f3a [kimi-k2.6] # ꔀ nitrologic Relay 1.8.6 ⛲  kimi-k2.6 🜁 🪠 🧊 $0.105 385.2KB 47.25s
1e968f3b [kimi-k2.6] #One change, and it is the one that matters:
1e968f3b [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f3b [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f3b [kimi-k2.6] #╭──────────────┬────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
1e968f3c [kimi-k2.6] #│  Location    │  Previous      │  Now                                                   │
1e968f3c [kimi-k2.6] #├──────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
1e968f3c [kimi-k2.6] #│  active loop │  `out pins, 1` │  `out pins, 2`                                         │
1e968f3c [kimi-k2.6] #╰──────────────┴────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯
1e968f3d [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f3d [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f3d [kimi-k2.6] #• What this fixes*
1e968f3d [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f3e [kimi-k2.6] #With `bitsPerPixel = 2` in `monobit.h`, the CPU emits two bits per pixel into the DMA buffer. `out
1e968f3e [kimi-k2.6] #pins, 1` discarded half of that data; `out pins, 2` shifts both bits onto `COLORPIN0` and
1e968f3e [kimi-k2.6] #`COLORPIN1` every 10 cycles, so the 2-bit colour index reaches `colortrain.pio` intact.
1e968f3e [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f3f [kimi-k2.6] #• Timing check*
1e968f3f [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f3f [kimi-k2.6] #The active loop is still exactly 10 cycles:
1e968f3f [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f40 [kimi-k2.6] #- `out pins, 2` → 1 cycle
1e968f40 [kimi-k2.6] #- `jmp y--, active [8]` → 1 cycle + 8 delay cycles = 9 cycles
1e968f40 [kimi-k2.6] #- Total = 10 cycles/pixel
1e968f40 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f41 [kimi-k2.6] #That preserves your PAL line lock (864 × 10 = 8640 cycles ≈ 51.9 µs active video).
1e968f41 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f41 [kimi-k2.6] #• Stale comment*
1e968f41 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e968f42 [kimi-k2.6] #The header still says `bitmap = [27 x 309/310]`, which reflected the old `bitsPerPixel = 1` word
1e968f42 [kimi-k2.6] #count. With `bitsPerPixel = 2`, `lineWords` is 54, so the DMA buffer the CPU builds is 54 words per
1e968f42 [kimi-k2.6] #active line. The PIO does not care (it just serially shifts bits from the FIFO), but anyone reading
1e968f42 [kimi-k2.6] #the code may be confused by the mismatch.
1e968f42 [kimi-k2.6] #
1e9697b7 [kimi-k2.6] # ꔀ nitrologic Relay 1.8.6 ⛲  kimi-k2.6 🜁 🪠 🧊 $0.121 388.9KB 28.40s
