1e97ee3b [gemini-3.1-lite] #Key Observations
1e97ee3c [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1e97ee3c [gemini-3.1-lite] #1.  System Design: The architecture adopts a modular pipeline approach where `pixelpump`
1e97ee3c [gemini-3.1-lite] #manages line-level timing, feeding bit-trains through `onebit` and `threepin` state machines to
1e97ee3c [gemini-3.1-lite] #drive the resistor-ladder DACs.
1e97ee3d [gemini-3.1-lite] #2.  Resource Utilization: The use of `piosmexec` to configure scratch registers
1e97ee3d [gemini-3.1-lite] #(`X`, `Y`) and the use of `FJOIN` modes to optimize FIFO usage demonstrates a deep utilization of
1e97ee3d [gemini-3.1-lite] #the RP2350’s PIO version 1 features.
1e97ee3d [gemini-3.1-lite] #3.  PAL/Chroma Timing: The `chroma.pio` and `initChroma` logic (calculating sine phases for
1e97ee3e [gemini-3.1-lite] #subcarrier generation) is a classic but complex implementation of composite video.
1e97ee3e [gemini-3.1-lite] #4.  Filesystem: The inclusion of `lfs` (LittleFS) integration indicates a robust approach
1e97ee3e [gemini-3.1-lite] #to storing assets (likely font maps or video frames) in flash memory.
1e97ee3e [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1e97ee3f [gemini-3.1-lite] #Potential Areas for Review
1e97ee3f [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1e97ee3f [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Instruction Memory Constraints: With 32 instructions per PIO block, complex programs like
1e97ee3f [gemini-3.1-lite] #the I2C driver or the `threepin` driver should be monitored for instruction density.
1e97ee40 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• DMA Pacing: The `viddmainit` function correctly uses DREQ to pace data, but
1e97ee40 [gemini-3.1-lite] #ensure that the `evenWords` and `oddWords` constants align strictly with the PAL line count to
1e97ee40 [gemini-3.1-lite] #prevent drift.
1e97ee40 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Chroma Stability: At 166.5 MHz, the `clkdiv` of `2.3471f` for chroma is extremely
1e97ee41 [gemini-3.1-lite] #sensitive. Ensure the system clock is stable, as any jitter in the 166.5 MHz source will manifest
1e97ee41 [gemini-3.1-lite] #as color phase noise.
1e97ee41 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1e97ee41 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Coding Style Suggestions
1e97ee42 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
