1eab6ccb [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab6ccb [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab6ccb [gemini-3.1-lite] #What happens if you skip it?
1eab6ccb [gemini-3.1-lite] #If you forget to call `piogpioinit`:
1eab6ccc [gemini-3.1-lite] #• The PIO peripheral will not be connected to that physical pin.
1eab6ccc [gemini-3.1-lite] #• The state machine will likely read a constant value (usually 0 or the last state of the internal
1eab6ccc [gemini-3.1-lite] #signal) regardless of what is happening on the actual wire.
1eab6ccc [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Your `jmp pin` instruction will behave unpredictably or fail to branch when you expect it to.
1eab6ccd [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab6ccd [gemini-3.1-lite] #A Note on Input Pins
1eab6ccd [gemini-3.1-lite] #If your `jmp` pin is strictly an input, you do not need to call
1eab6ccd [gemini-3.1-lite] #`piosmsetconsecutivepindirs` for that specific pin, as that function is intended
