1eab79de [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79de [gemini-3.1-lite] #1. The `pixelpump` Pipeline
1eab79de [gemini-3.1-lite] #Your `pixelpump` -> `onebit` -> `threepin` architecture is an interesting way to manage a 3-lane
1eab79de [gemini-3.1-lite] #video pipeline.
1eab79df [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Pipeline Stall Risk: Because you are using `pull block` and `push block` heavily, any
1eab79df [gemini-3.1-lite] #jitter in the system DMA or FIFO access will cause the state machines to stall. Since video timing
1eab79df [gemini-3.1-lite] #(PAL 576i) is strictly synchronous, ensure your DMA channels are configured with high priority and
1eab79df [gemini-3.1-lite] #that your `pixelpump` program provides a sufficient "look-ahead" buffer to prevent underflow.
1eab79e0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Instruction Density: You are using `out pindirs, 3` repeatedly in `threepin`. On RP2350,
1eab79e0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #you now have the `mov pindirs, x` instruction. If you can pre-calculate the pindir states in
1eab79e0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #memory, `mov pindirs, x` might be significantly more efficient than unrolling the `out`
1eab79e0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #instructions.
1eab79e0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79e0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #2. `threepin.pio` - Alpha Bits
1eab79e0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #You mentioned `out null, 2` for the 2-bit alpha skip.
1eab79e1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Optimization: If you ever need more headroom, remember that on RP2350, the `MOV`
1eab79e1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #instruction can now manipulate `PINDIRS`. If your alpha/blanking logic is static, you might be able
1eab79e1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #to use `MOV` to switch entire banks of pins between high-impedance and output mode in a single
1eab79e1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #cycle, rather than shifting through a bit-train.
1eab79e2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79e2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #3. `onebit.pio` - Loopback Pin
1eab79e2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #You noted the need for a "single loopback pin for pixel state GPIO 46".
1eab79e2 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Safety: Ensure that GPIO 46 is not configured for any other peripheral. Since you are
1eab79e3 [gemini-3.1-lite] #using it as a state-branching pin (`jmp pin`), ensure `piogpioinit` is called, and consider
1eab79e3 [gemini-3.1-lite] #if you need to set the input synchronizer bypass (`INPUTSYNCBYPASS`) for that pin to save
1eab79e3 [gemini-3.1-lite] #the 2-cycle synchronization latency if your timing budget is tight.
1eab79e4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79e4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #4. `colortrain.pio` (The new file)
1eab79e4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #This seems to be a variation of your `greyline.pio`.
1eab79e4 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• `rxfifo[y]` usage: You are using `mov osr, rxfifo[y]`. This is a powerful RP2350 feature.
1eab79e5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #Ensure `SHIFTCTRLFJOINRX_GET` is correctly configured in your C++ init code, or this
1eab79e5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #instruction will trigger undefined behavior.
1eab79e5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• IRQ 6: You are waiting on `irq 6`. In your `vidbit.pio`, you have `irq next set 6`. This
1eab79e5 [gemini-3.1-lite] #is excellent usage of the new RP2350 cross-PIO IRQ capability. It keeps the timing of the
1eab79e6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #`colortrain` strictly locked to the `vidbit` line timing.
1eab79e6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79e6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #5. C++ Integration (General)
1eab79e6 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Atomic Updates: Since you are doing video, you are likely double-buffering. Ensure that
1eab79e7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #when you update the `evenFrame` or `oddFrame` arrays, you use
1eab79e7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #`dmachanneltransferfrombuffer_now` or similar to avoid tearing.
1eab79e7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• JSON Parser: You included a JSON parser. If this is used for configuring video parameters
1eab79e7 [gemini-3.1-lite] #at runtime, ensure the parser is not running on the same core that is servicing the PIO DMA
1eab79e8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #interrupts, as the parser's memory allocation/deallocation could introduce latency spikes that
1eab79e8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #cause the video to jitter.
1eab79e8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79e8 [gemini-3.1-lite] #A Quick Suggestion on `vidbit.pio`
1eab79e9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #In `vidbit.pio`, you have:
1eab79e9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79e9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #pedestal:
1eab79e9 [gemini-3.1-lite] #    set pindirs, 1 [2]
1eab79ea [gemini-3.1-lite] #nextpixel:
1eab79ea [gemini-3.1-lite] #    jmp y--, active [6]
1eab79ea [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79ea [gemini-3.1-lite] #If you find you are running out of cycles for high-resolution modes, check if you can use the `MOV`
1eab79eb [gemini-3.1-lite] #instruction to update `PINDIRS` in bulk, as noted above. It is significantly faster than `SET` or
1eab79eb [gemini-3.1-lite] #`OUT` for large groups of pins.
1eab79eb [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1eab79eb [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Are you planning to use the new RP2350 `MOV PINDIRS, x` instruction to optimize the
1eab79ec [gemini-3.1-lite] #`threepin` output stage?* It could potentially collapse your `out pindirs, 3` unrolled loop
1eab79ec [gemini-3.1-lite] #into a single cycle.
1eab79ec [gemini-3.1-lite] #
