1ed151a0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Key points:*
1ed151a0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Namespace: It resides in the `std` namespace.
1ed151a0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Persistence: Unlike manipulators like `std::setprecision` or `std::setbase`, `std::setw`
1ed151a0 [gemini-3.1-lite] #is non-persistent. It only affects the single next output operation. After that, the width
1ed151a1 [gemini-3.1-lite] #resets to the default (which is usually just enough space to fit the content).
