1ed1d87c [gemini-3.1-lite] #To decode S/PDIF using PIO, we need to detect transitions (Biphase Mark Code). In BMC, a transition
1ed1d87d [gemini-3.1-lite] #occurs at every bit boundary, and an additional transition occurs in the middle of the bit period
1ed1d87d [gemini-3.1-lite] #if the data is a `1`.
1ed1d87d [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1ed1d87d [gemini-3.1-lite] #Since you are running at 148.5 MHz, we can use the `in` instruction to sample the pin and
1ed1d87e [gemini-3.1-lite] #the `jmp` instruction to detect transitions.
1ed1d87e [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1ed1d87e [gemini-3.1-lite] #Here is a PIO program structure to handle the sampling. This uses a "wait for transition" approach.
1ed1d87e [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1ed1d87f [gemini-3.1-lite] #
