1ed2831e [gemini-3.1-lite] #• Direction: You are now correctly reading from `&pio->rxf[sm]` and writing to
1ed2831e [gemini-3.1-lite] #`audioWordBuffer`.
1ed2831e [gemini-3.1-lite] #• DREQ: Using `piogetdreq(pio, sm, false)` correctly synchronizes the DMA with the
1ed2831e [gemini-3.1-lite] #PIO's internal FIFO status.
1ed2831f [gemini-3.1-lite] #
1ed2831f [gemini-3.1-lite] #Your code is now ready to be integrated into your main loop or task handler. If you find that the
1ed2831f [gemini-3.1-lite] #audio stream is "popping" or stuttering, it is usually an indicator that the DMA is not being
