1f2874cb [kimi-k2.6] #
1f2874cb [kimi-k2.6] #• How it works*
1f2874cb [kimi-k2.6] #
1f2874cb [kimi-k2.6] #• Rgnd (1 MΩ) provides the DC path to ground that the guitar needs and sets the AC input
1f2874cb [kimi-k2.6] #impedance to about 500 kΩ (acceptable for most pickups).
1f2874cb [kimi-k2.6] #• C1 blocks DC. With Rin it forms a high-pass filter at ~1.6 Hz, preserving low
1f2874cb [kimi-k2.6] #E-string fundamentals.
1f2874cc [kimi-k2.6] #• Rin (1 MΩ) and Rf (470 kΩ) set an AC gain of –0.47. A hot ±3 V guitar
1f2874cc [kimi-k2.6] #signal is reduced to about ±1.4 V, keeping the output inside the 0 V – 3.3 V rails with the 1.65 V
1f2874cc [kimi-k2.6] #bias.
1f2874cc [kimi-k2.6] #• Rb1/Rb2 (100 kΩ each) bias the op-amp’s non-inverting input at 1.65 V. Cb
1f2874cd [kimi-k2.6] #keeps that reference quiet.
1f2874cd [kimi-k2.6] #• Because the input is AC-coupled, the op-amp’s DC gain is 1, so the output rests at 1.65 V with no
1f2874cd [kimi-k2.6] #signal.
1f2874cd [kimi-k2.6] #• Rout (1 kΩ) and the Schottky clamp diodes D1/D2 protect the ADC pin from
1f2874ce [kimi-k2.6] #transients that exceed 0 V – 3.3 V.
1f2874ce [kimi-k2.6] #• Cfilter (100 pF) at the ADC pin tames sampling glitches.
1f2874ce [kimi-k2.6] #
