1f2874e0 [kimi-k2.6] #Usage Tips
1f2874e0 [kimi-k2.6] #
1f2874e1 [kimi-k2.6] #• ADC reference: The Pico defaults to a 3.3 V reference. With no guitar plugged in, the ADC
1f2874e1 [kimi-k2.6] #should read roughly half-scale (~2048 for 12-bit raw).
1f2874e1 [kimi-k2.6] #• Sampling rate: In the passive version, the ADC is driven through a high resistance. If
1f2874e1 [kimi-k2.6] #you sample too fast the reading may bleed between channels or settle poorly; either add a small
1f2874e2 [kimi-k2.6] #delay between readings or reduce the ADC clock.
1f2874e2 [kimi-k2.6] #• Op-amp stability: Keep leads to the MCP6002 short and place the 100 nF decoupling cap
1f2874e2 [kimi-k2.6] #directly across its supply pins.
1f2874e2 [kimi-k2.6] #• Shielding: Use shielded cable between the RCA jack and the board, and keep the analog
1f2874e3 [kimi-k2.6] #section away from the Pico’s switching regulator if possible.
1f2874e3 [kimi-k2.6] #
1f289354 [nitro@ryzen5] circuit to measure paddle pinsatari 9 pin from pico?
1f28a10f [kimi-k2.6] # ꔀ nitrologic Relay 1.8.7 ⛲  kimi-k2.6 🜁 🪠 🧊 $0.049 8.588KB 219.10s
1f28a10f [kimi-k2.6] #Atari paddles are passive: each is just a 1 MΩ (approx.) potentiometer wired as a two-terminal
1f28a10f [kimi-k2.6] #rheostat between the +V pin and the sense pin, plus a momentary button that shorts to ground.
1f28a110 [kimi-k2.6] #The original Atari console measured them by discharging a capacitor and timing how long it took to
1f28a110 [kimi-k2.6] #charge back through the pot. You can replicate that exactly with the Pico’s GPIOs—no ADC
1f28a110 [kimi-k2.6] #required—which avoids the high source-impedance headaches you get trying to read a 1 MΩ divider
1f28a110 [kimi-k2.6] #directly.
1f28a111 [kimi-k2.6] #
1f28a111 [kimi-k2.6] #Below is the recommended GPIO RC-timing circuit, plus a simpler ADC fallback if you
1f28a111 [kimi-k2.6] #prefer a voltage-based approach.
1f28a111 [kimi-k2.6] #
1f28a112 [kimi-k2.6] #━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1f28a112 [kimi-k2.6] #
1f28a112 [kimi-k2.6] #Atari DE-9 Pinout (Paddle Functions)
1f28a112 [kimi-k2.6] #
1f28a113 [kimi-k2.6] #╭───────────┬───────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────╮
1f28a113 [kimi-k2.6] #│  DB9 Pin  │  Paddle Function              │  Direction                 │
1f28a113 [kimi-k2.6] #├───────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
1f28a114 [kimi-k2.6] #│  1        │  Button A (Left)              │  Active-low → GND          │
1f28a114 [kimi-k2.6] #│  2        │  Button B (Right)             │  Active-low → GND          │
1f28a114 [kimi-k2.6] #│  5        │  Potentiometer B (wiper)      │  Input to Pico             │
1f28a114 [kimi-k2.6] #│  7        │  +5 V (excitation)            │  Output **from** Pico 3V3  │
1f28a115 [kimi-k2.6] #│  8        │  GND                          │  Common ground             │
1f28a115 [kimi-k2.6] #│  9        │  Potentiometer A (wiper)      │  Input to Pico             │
1f28a115 [kimi-k2.6] #│  3, 4, 6  │  Unused for standard paddles  │  —                         │
