1f648840 [gpt-5.3-codex] #- No `SetCommTimeouts` call (write can wait a long time or appear hung).
1f648840 [gpt-5.3-codex] #- Flow control mismatch (RTS/CTS or XON/XOFF enabled on one side, not the other).
1f648840 [gpt-5.3-codex] #- Device not actually consuming data (driver/USB-serial stack can stall writes).
1f648840 [gpt-5.3-codex] #- Port opened by another process previously in odd state.
1f648841 [gpt-5.3-codex] #- Large write buffer + blocked downstream endpoint (less likely for `"\nBOOT\n"` but
1f648841 [gpt-5.3-codex] #possible with bad state).
